  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prologue'
      title: Prologue
      number: 1
      content: 'The former account I made, O Theophilus, of all that Jesus began
        both to do and teach, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'until the day in which He was taken up, after He through the Holy
        Spirit had given commandments to the apostles whom He had chosen, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Holy Spirit Promised'
      title: The Holy Spirit Promised
      number: 3
      content: to whom He also presented Himself alive after His suffering by many
        infallible proofs, being seen by them during forty days and speaking of the
        things pertaining to the kingdom of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And being assembled together with them, He commanded them not to
        depart from Jerusalem, but to wait for the Promise of the Father, <JESUS>\u201Cwhich,\u201D</JESUS> 
        He  said,  <JESUS>\u201Cyou have </JESUS><JESUS>heard from Me;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "<JESUS>for John truly baptized with water, </JESUS><JESUS>but you
        shall be baptized with the Holy Spirit not many days from now.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore, when they had come together, they asked Him, saying, \u201CLord,
        will You at this time restore the kingdom to Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And He said to them, <JESUS>\u201CIt is not for you to </JESUS><JESUS>know
        times or seasons which the Father has put in His own authority.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Jesus Ascends to Heaven'
      title: Jesus Ascends to Heaven
      number: 8
      content: "<JESUS>But you shall receive power </JESUS><JESUS>when the Holy Spirit
        has come upon you; and </JESUS><JESUS>you shall be </JESUS><JESUS>witnesses
        to Me</JESUS><JESUS> in Jerusalem, and in all Judea and </JESUS><JESUS>Samaria,
        and to the </JESUS><JESUS>end of the earth.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now when He had spoken these things, while they watched, He was taken
        up, and a cloud received Him out of their sight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And while they looked steadfastly toward heaven as He went up, behold,
        two men stood by them in white apparel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Upper Room Prayer Meeting'
      title: The Upper Room Prayer Meeting
      number: 11
      content: "who also said, \u201CMen of Galilee, why do you stand gazing up into
        heaven? This same Jesus, who was taken up from you into heaven, will so come
        in like manner as you saw Him go into heaven.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then they returned to Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet, which
        is near Jerusalem, a Sabbath day\u2019s journey. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And when they had entered, they went up into the upper room where
        they were staying: Peter, James, John, and Andrew; Philip and Thomas; Bartholomew
        and Matthew; James the  son of Alphaeus and Simon the Zealot; and Judas the 
        son of James. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Matthias Chosen'
      title: Matthias Chosen
      number: 14
      content: These all continued with one accord in prayer and supplication, with
        the women and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with His brothers.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And in those days Peter stood up in the midst of the disciples (altogether
        the number of names was about a hundred and twenty), and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CMen and brethren, this Scripture had to be fulfilled, which
        the Holy Spirit spoke before by the mouth of David concerning Judas, who
        became a guide to those who arrested Jesus; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "for he was numbered with us and obtained a part in this ministry.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '(Now this man purchased a field with the wages of iniquity; and falling
        headlong, he burst open in the middle and all his entrails gushed out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And it became known to all those dwelling in Jerusalem; so that field
        is called in their own language, Akel Dama, that is, Field of Blood.)
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CFor it is written in the Book of Psalms:\u2018Let his dwelling
        place be desolate,And let no one live in it\u2019;and,\u2018Let another take
        his office.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CTherefore, of these men who have accompanied us all the time
        that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "beginning from the baptism of John to that day when He was taken
        up from us, one of these must become a witness with us of His resurrection.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they proposed two: Joseph called Barsabas, who was surnamed Justus,
        and Matthias. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And they prayed and said, \u201CYou, O Lord, who know the hearts
        of all, show which of these two You have chosen "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "to take part in this ministry and apostleship from which Judas by
        transgression fell, that he might go to his own place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And they cast their lots, and the lot fell on Matthias. And he was
        numbered with the eleven apostles.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Coming of the Holy Spirit'
      title: Coming of the Holy Spirit
      number: 1
      content: 'When the Day of Pentecost had fully come, they were all with one
        accord in one place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And suddenly there came a sound from heaven, as of a rushing mighty
        wind, and it filled the whole house where they were sitting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then there appeared to them divided tongues, as of fire, and one
        sat upon each of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: The Crowd\u2019s Response"
      title: "The Crowd\u2019s Response"
      number: 4
      content: And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak with
        other tongues, as the Spirit gave them utterance.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And there were dwelling in Jerusalem Jews, devout men, from every
        nation under heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when this sound occurred, the multitude came together, and were
        confused, because everyone heard them speak in his own language. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then they were all amazed and marveled, saying to one another, \u201CLook,
        are not all these who speak Galileans? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And how is  it  that we hear, each in our own language in which we
        were born? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Parthians and Medes and Elamites, those dwelling in Mesopotamia,
        Judea and Cappadocia, Pontus and Asia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Phrygia and Pamphylia, Egypt and the parts of Libya adjoining Cyrene,
        visitors from Rome, both Jews and proselytes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Cretans and Arabs\u2014we hear them speaking in our own tongues the
        wonderful works of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So they were all amazed and perplexed, saying to one another, \u201CWhatever
        could this mean?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Peter\u2019s Sermon"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Sermon"
      number: 13
      content: "Others mocking said, \u201CThey are full of new wine.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Peter, standing up with the eleven, raised his voice and said
        to them, \u201CMen of Judea and all who dwell in Jerusalem, let this be known
        to you, and heed my words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For these are not drunk, as you suppose, since it is only the third
        hour of the day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But this is what was spoken by the prophet Joel:'
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018And it shall come to pass in the last days, says God,That I
        will pour out of My Spirit on all flesh;Your sons and your daughters shall
        prophesy,Your young men shall see visions,Your old men shall dream dreams."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And on My menservants and on My maidservantsI will pour out My Spirit
        in those days;And they shall prophesy.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: I will show wonders in heaven aboveAnd signs in the earth beneath:Blood
        and fire and vapor of smoke.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The sun shall be turned into darkness,And the moon into blood,Before
        the coming of the great and awesome day of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And it shall come to passThat  whoever calls on the name of the LordShall
        be saved.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CMen of Israel, hear these words: Jesus of Nazareth, a Man attested
        by God to you by miracles, wonders, and signs which God did through Him in
        your midst, as you yourselves also know\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Him, being delivered by the determined purpose and foreknowledge
        of God, you have taken by lawless hands, have crucified, and put to death; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'whom God raised up, having loosed the pains of death, because it
        was not possible that He should be held by it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For David says concerning Him:\u2018I foresaw the Lord always before
        my face,For He is at my right hand, that I may not be shaken."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Therefore my heart rejoiced, and my tongue was glad;Moreover my flesh
        also will rest in hope.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: For You will not leave my soul in Hades,Nor will You allow Your Holy
        One to see corruption.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You have made known to me the ways of life;You will make me full
        of joy in Your presence.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CMen and brethren, let me speak freely to you of the patriarch
        David, that he is both dead and buried, and his tomb is with us to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Therefore, being a prophet, and knowing that God had sworn with an
        oath to him that of the fruit of his body, according to the flesh, He would
        raise up the Christ to sit on his throne, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'he, foreseeing this, spoke concerning the resurrection of the Christ,
        that His soul was not left in Hades, nor did His flesh see corruption. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'This Jesus God has raised up, of which we are all witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Therefore being exalted to the right hand of God, and having received
        from the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, He poured out this which
        you now see and hear.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CFor David did not ascend into the heavens, but he says himself:\u2018The
        Lord said to my Lord,\u201CSit at My right hand,"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Till I make Your enemies Your footstool.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CTherefore let all the house of Israel know assuredly that God
        has made this Jesus, whom you crucified, both Lord and Christ.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Now when they heard this,  they were cut to the heart, and said to
        Peter and the rest of the apostles, \u201CMen and brethren, what shall we
        do?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then Peter said to them, \u201CRepent, and let every one of you be
        baptized in the name of Jesus Christ for the remission of sins; and you shall
        receive the gift of the Holy Spirit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: A Vital Church Grows'
      title: A Vital Church Grows
      number: 39
      content: "For the promise is to you and to your children, and to all who are
        afar off, as many as the Lord our God will call.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And with many other words he testified and exhorted them, saying,
        \u201CBe saved from this perverse generation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then those who gladly received his word were baptized; and that day
        about three thousand souls were added to  them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "And they continued steadfastly in the apostles\u2019 doctrine and
        fellowship, in the breaking of bread, and in prayers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Then fear came upon every soul, and many wonders and signs were done
        through the apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Now all who believed were together, and had all things in common, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: and sold their possessions and goods, and divided them among all,
        as anyone had need.
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'So continuing daily with one accord in the temple, and breaking bread
        from house to house, they ate their food with gladness and simplicity of
        heart, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: praising God and having favor with all the people. And the Lord added
        to the church daily those who were being saved.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Lame Man Healed'
      title: A Lame Man Healed
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Peter and John went up together to the temple at the hour of
        prayer, the ninth hour.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And a certain man lame from his mother\u2019s womb was carried, whom
        they laid daily at the gate of the temple which is called Beautiful, to ask
        alms from those who entered the temple; "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'who, seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple, asked for
        alms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And fixing his eyes on him, with John, Peter said, \u201CLook at
        us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So he gave them his attention, expecting to receive something from
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Peter said, \u201CSilver and gold I do not have, but what I
        do have I give you: In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, rise up and
        walk.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he took him by the right hand and lifted him up, and immediately
        his feet and ankle bones received strength. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So he, leaping up, stood and walked and entered the temple with them\u2014walking,
        leaping, and praising God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And all the people saw him walking and praising God. '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Preaching in Solomon\u2019s Portico"
      title: "Preaching in Solomon\u2019s Portico"
      number: 10
      content: Then they knew that it was he who sat begging alms at the Beautiful
        Gate of the temple; and they were filled with wonder and amazement at what
        had happened to him.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now as the lame man who was healed held on to Peter and John, all
        the people ran together to them in the porch which is called Solomon\u2019s,
        greatly amazed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So when Peter saw it, he responded to the people: \u201CMen of Israel,
        why do you marvel at this? Or why look so intently at us, as though by our
        own power or godliness we had made this man walk? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The God of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, the God of our fathers, glorified
        His Servant Jesus, whom you delivered up and denied in the presence of Pilate,
        when he was determined to let Him go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But you denied the Holy One and the Just, and asked for a murderer
        to be granted to you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and killed the Prince of life, whom God raised from the dead, of
        which we are witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And His name, through faith in His name, has made this man strong,
        whom you see and know. Yes, the faith which comes through Him has given him
        this perfect soundness in the presence of you all.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYet now, brethren, I know that you did it in ignorance, as
        did also your rulers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But those things which God foretold by the mouth of all His prophets,
        that the Christ would suffer, He has thus fulfilled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Repent therefore and be converted, that your sins may be blotted
        out, so that times of refreshing may come from the presence of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and that He may send Jesus Christ, who was preached to you before, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'whom heaven must receive until the times of restoration of all things,
        which God has spoken by the mouth of all His holy prophets since the world
        began. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For Moses truly said to the fathers, \u2018The Lord your God will
        raise up for you a Prophet like me from your brethren. Him you shall hear
        in all things, whatever He says to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And it shall be that every soul who will not hear that Prophet shall
        be utterly destroyed from among the people.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Yes, and all the prophets, from Samuel and those who follow, as many
        as have spoken, have also foretold these days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "You are sons of the prophets, and of the covenant which God made
        with our fathers, saying to Abraham, \u2018And in your seed all the families
        of the earth shall be blessed.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "To you first, God, having raised up His Servant Jesus, sent Him to
        bless you, in turning away every one of  you from your iniquities.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Peter and John Arrested'
      title: Peter and John Arrested
      number: 1
      content: 'Now as they spoke to the people, the priests, the captain of the
        temple, and the Sadducees came upon them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'being greatly disturbed that they taught the people and preached
        in Jesus the resurrection from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And they laid hands on them, and put them in custody until the next
        day, for it was already evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Addressing the Sanhedrin'
      title: Addressing the Sanhedrin
      number: 4
      content: However, many of those who heard the word believed; and the number
        of the men came to be about five thousand.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And it came to pass, on the next day, that their rulers, elders,
        and scribes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'as well as Annas the high priest, Caiaphas, John, and Alexander,
        and as many as were of the family of the high priest, were gathered together
        at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And when they had set them in the midst, they asked, \u201CBy what
        power or by what name have you done this?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit, said to them, \u201CRulers
        of the people and elders of Israel: "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If we this day are judged for a good deed done to a helpless man,
        by what means he has been made well, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'let it be known to you all, and to all the people of Israel, that
        by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom you crucified, whom God raised
        from the dead, by Him this man stands here before you whole. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "This is the \u2018stone which was rejected by you builders, which
        has become the chief cornerstone.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Name of Jesus Forbidden'
      title: The Name of Jesus Forbidden
      number: 12
      content: "Nor is there salvation in any other, for there is no other name under
        heaven given among men by which we must be saved.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that
        they were uneducated and untrained men, they marveled. And they realized
        that they had been with Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And seeing the man who had been healed standing with them, they could
        say nothing against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But when they had commanded them to go aside out of the council,
        they conferred among themselves, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "saying, \u201CWhat shall we do to these men? For, indeed, that a
        notable miracle has been done through them is  evident to all who dwell in
        Jerusalem, and we cannot deny it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But so that it spreads no further among the people, let us severely
        threaten them, that from now on they speak to no man in this name.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So they called them and commanded them not to speak at all nor teach
        in the name of Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Peter and John answered and said to them, \u201CWhether it is
        right in the sight of God to listen to you more than to God, you judge. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For we cannot but speak the things which we have seen and heard.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So when they had further threatened them, they let them go, finding
        no way of punishing them, because of the people, since they all glorified
        God for what had been done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Prayer for Boldness'
      title: Prayer for Boldness
      number: 22
      content: For the man was over forty years old on whom this miracle of healing
        had been performed.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And being let go, they went to their own companions and reported
        all that the chief priests and elders had said to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So when they heard that, they raised their voice to God with one
        accord and said: \u201CLord, You are God, who made heaven and earth and the
        sea, and all that is in them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "who by the mouth of Your servant David have said:\u2018Why did the
        nations rage,And the people plot vain things?"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "The kings of the earth took their stand,And the rulers were gathered
        togetherAgainst the Lord and against His Christ.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CFor truly against Your holy Servant Jesus, whom You anointed,
        both Herod and Pontius Pilate, with the Gentiles and the people of Israel,
        were gathered together "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'to do whatever Your hand and Your purpose determined before to be
        done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now, Lord, look on their threats, and grant to Your servants that
        with all boldness they may speak Your word, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "by stretching out Your hand to heal, and that signs and wonders may
        be done through the name of Your holy Servant Jesus.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Sharing in All Things'
      title: Sharing in All Things
      number: 31
      content: And when they had prayed, the place where they were assembled together
        was shaken; and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and they spoke
        the word of God with boldness.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now the multitude of those who believed were of one heart and one
        soul; neither did anyone say that any of the things he possessed was his
        own, but they had all things in common. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And with great power the apostles gave witness to the resurrection
        of the Lord Jesus. And great grace was upon them all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Nor was there anyone among them who lacked; for all who were possessors
        of lands or houses sold them, and brought the proceeds of the things that
        were sold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "and laid them at the apostles\u2019 feet; and they distributed to
        each as anyone had need."
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And Joses, who was also named Barnabas by the apostles (which is
        translated Son of Encouragement), a Levite of the country of Cyprus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "having land, sold it, and brought the money and laid it at the apostles\u2019
        feet."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Lying to the Holy Spirit'
      title: Lying to the Holy Spirit
      number: 1
      content: 'But a certain man named Ananias, with Sapphira his wife, sold a possession. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he kept back part of the proceeds, his wife also being aware
        of  it, and brought a certain part and laid it at the apostles\u2019 feet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Peter said, \u201CAnanias, why has Satan filled your heart to
        lie to the Holy Spirit and keep back part of the price of the land for yourself? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "While it remained, was it not your own? And after it was sold, was
        it not in your own control? Why have you conceived this thing in your heart?
        You have not lied to men but to God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Ananias, hearing these words, fell down and breathed his last.
        So great fear came upon all those who heard these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And the young men arose and wrapped him up, carried him out, and buried
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now it was about three hours later when his wife came in, not knowing
        what had happened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Peter answered her, \u201CTell me whether you sold the land for
        so much?\u201DShe said, \u201CYes, for so much.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Peter said to her, \u201CHow is it that you have agreed together
        to test the Spirit of the Lord? Look, the feet of those who have buried your
        husband are at the door, and they will carry you out.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then immediately she fell down at his feet and breathed her last.
        And the young men came in and found her dead, and carrying her out, buried
        her by her husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Continuing Power in the Church'
      title: Continuing Power in the Church
      number: 11
      content: So great fear came upon all the church and upon all who heard these
        things.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And through the hands of the apostles many signs and wonders were
        done among the people. And they were all with one accord in Solomon\u2019s
        Porch. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet none of the rest dared join them, but the people esteemed them
        highly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And believers were increasingly added to the Lord, multitudes of
        both men and women, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'so that they brought the sick out into the streets and laid them
        on beds and couches, that at least the shadow of Peter passing by might fall
        on some of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Imprisoned Apostles Freed'
      title: Imprisoned Apostles Freed
      number: 16
      content: Also a multitude gathered from the surrounding cities to Jerusalem,
        bringing sick people and those who were tormented by unclean spirits, and
        they were all healed.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the high priest rose up, and all those who were with him (which
        is the sect of the Sadducees), and they were filled with indignation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and laid their hands on the apostles and put them in the common prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But at night an angel of the Lord opened the prison doors and brought
        them out, and said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CGo, stand in the temple and speak to the people all the words
        of this life.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Apostles on Trial Again'
      title: Apostles on Trial Again
      number: 21
      content: And when they heard that, they entered the temple early in the morning
        and taught. But the high priest and those with him came and called the council
        together, with all the elders of the children of Israel, and sent to the
        prison to have them brought.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But when the officers came and did not find them in the prison, they
        returned and reported, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "saying, \u201CIndeed we found the prison shut securely, and the guards
        standing outside before the doors; but when we opened them, we found no one
        inside!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now when the high priest, the captain of the temple, and the chief
        priests heard these things, they wondered what the outcome would be. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So one came and told them, saying, \u201CLook, the men whom you put
        in prison are standing in the temple and teaching the people!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then the captain went with the officers and brought them without
        violence, for they feared the people, lest they should be stoned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And when they had brought them, they set them before the council.
        And the high priest asked them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "saying, \u201CDid we not strictly command you not to teach in this
        name? And look, you have filled Jerusalem with your doctrine, and intend
        to bring this Man\u2019s blood on us!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But Peter and the other apostles answered and said: \u201CWe ought
        to obey God rather than men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The God of our fathers raised up Jesus whom you murdered by hanging
        on a tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Him God has exalted to His right hand to  be  Prince and Savior,
        to give repentance to Israel and forgiveness of sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: "32: Gamaliel\u2019s Advice"
      title: "Gamaliel\u2019s Advice"
      number: 32
      content: "And we are His witnesses to these things, and so also is the Holy
        Spirit whom God has given to those who obey Him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When they heard this, they were furious and plotted to kill them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then one in the council stood up, a Pharisee named Gamaliel, a teacher
        of the law held in respect by all the people, and commanded them to put the
        apostles outside for a little while. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And he said to them: \u201CMen of Israel, take heed to yourselves
        what you intend to do regarding these men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For some time ago Theudas rose up, claiming to be somebody. A number
        of men, about four hundred, joined him. He was slain, and all who obeyed
        him were scattered and came to nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'After this man, Judas of Galilee rose up in the days of the census,
        and drew away many people after him. He also perished, and all who obeyed
        him were dispersed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And now I say to you, keep away from these men and let them alone;
        for if this plan or this work is of men, it will come to nothing; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "but if it is of God, you cannot overthrow it\u2014lest you even be
        found to fight against God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And they agreed with him, and when they had called for the apostles
        and beaten them, they commanded that they should not speak in the name of
        Jesus, and let them go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'So they departed from the presence of the council, rejoicing that
        they were counted worthy to suffer shame for His name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: And daily in the temple, and in every house, they did not cease teaching
        and preaching Jesus as the Christ.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Seven Chosen to Serve'
      title: Seven Chosen to Serve
      number: 1
      content: 'Now in those days, when the  number  of the disciples was multiplying,
        there arose a complaint against the Hebrews by the Hellenists, because their
        widows were neglected in the daily distribution. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then the twelve summoned the multitude of the disciples and said,
        \u201CIt is not desirable that we should leave the word of God and serve
        tables. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore, brethren, seek out from among you seven men of good reputation,
        full of the Holy Spirit and wisdom, whom we may appoint over this business; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "but we will give ourselves continually to prayer and to the ministry
        of the word.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the saying pleased the whole multitude. And they chose Stephen,
        a man full of faith and the Holy Spirit, and Philip, Prochorus, Nicanor,
        Timon, Parmenas, and Nicolas, a proselyte from Antioch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: whom they set before the apostles; and when they had prayed, they
        laid hands on them.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Stephen Accused of Blasphemy'
      title: Stephen Accused of Blasphemy
      number: 7
      content: Then the word of God spread, and the number of the disciples multiplied
        greatly in Jerusalem, and a great many of the priests were obedient to the
        faith.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Stephen, full of faith and power, did great wonders and signs
        among the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then there arose some from what is called the Synagogue of the Freedmen
        (Cyrenians, Alexandrians, and those from Cilicia and Asia), disputing with
        Stephen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they were not able to resist the wisdom and the Spirit by which
        he spoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then they secretly induced men to say, \u201CWe have heard him speak
        blasphemous words against Moses and God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they stirred up the people, the elders, and the scribes; and
        they came upon him, seized him, and brought him to the council. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They also set up false witnesses who said, \u201CThis man does not
        cease to speak blasphemous words against this holy place and the law; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "for we have heard him say that this Jesus of Nazareth will destroy
        this place and change the customs which Moses delivered to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And all who sat in the council, looking steadfastly at him, saw his
        face as the face of an angel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Stephen\u2019s Address: The Call of Abraham"
      title: "Stephen\u2019s Address: The Call of Abraham"
      number: 1
      content: "Then the high priest said, \u201CAre these things so?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said, \u201CBrethren and fathers, listen: The God of glory
        appeared to our father Abraham when he was in Mesopotamia, before he dwelt
        in Haran, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and said to him, \u2018Get out of your country and from your relatives,
        and come to a land that I will show you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then he came out of the land of the Chaldeans and dwelt in Haran.
        And from there, when his father was dead, He moved him to this land in which
        you now dwell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And God gave him no inheritance in it, not even enough to set his
        foot on. But even when Abraham had no child, He promised to give it to him
        for a possession, and to his descendants after him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But God spoke in this way: that his descendants would dwell in a
        foreign land, and that they would bring them into bondage and oppress them
        four hundred years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018And the nation to whom they will be in bondage I will judge,\u2019
        said God, \u2018and after that they shall come out and serve Me in this place.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Patriarchs in Egypt'
      title: The Patriarchs in Egypt
      number: 8
      content: Then He gave him the covenant of circumcision; and so Abraham begot
        Isaac and circumcised him on the eighth day; and Isaac begot Jacob, and Jacob
        begot the twelve patriarchs.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd the patriarchs, becoming envious, sold Joseph into Egypt.
        But God was with him "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and delivered him out of all his troubles, and gave him favor and
        wisdom in the presence of Pharaoh, king of Egypt; and he made him governor
        over Egypt and all his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now a famine and great trouble came over all the land of Egypt and
        Canaan, and our fathers found no sustenance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when Jacob heard that there was grain in Egypt, he sent out our
        fathers first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the second time Joseph was made known to his brothers, and Joseph\u2019s
        family became known to the Pharaoh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Joseph sent and called his father Jacob and all his relatives
        to him, seventy-five people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Jacob went down to Egypt; and he died, he and our fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: God Delivers Israel by Moses'
      title: God Delivers Israel by Moses
      number: 16
      content: And they were carried back to Shechem and laid in the tomb that Abraham
        bought for a sum of money from the sons of Hamor, the  father of Shechem.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut when the time of the promise drew near which God had sworn
        to Abraham, the people grew and multiplied in Egypt "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'till another king arose who did not know Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'This man dealt treacherously with our people, and oppressed our forefathers,
        making them expose their babies, so that they might not live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "At this time Moses was born, and was well pleasing to God; and he
        was brought up in his father\u2019s house for three months. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But when he was set out, Pharaoh\u2019s daughter took him away and
        brought him up as her own son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And Moses was learned in all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and was
        mighty in words and deeds.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CNow when he was forty years old, it came into his heart to
        visit his brethren, the children of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And seeing one of them suffer wrong, he defended and avenged him
        who was oppressed, and struck down the Egyptian. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For he supposed that his brethren would have understood that God
        would deliver them by his hand, but they did not understand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And the next day he appeared to two  of them as they were fighting,
        and tried  to reconcile them, saying, \u2018Men, you are brethren; why do
        you wrong one another?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But he who did his neighbor wrong pushed him away, saying, \u2018Who
        made you a ruler and a judge over us? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Do you want to kill me as you did the Egyptian yesterday?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Then, at this saying, Moses fled and became a dweller in the land
        of Midian, where he had two sons.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CAnd when forty years had passed, an Angel of the Lord appeared
        to him in a flame of fire in a bush, in the wilderness of Mount Sinai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When Moses saw it, he marveled at the sight; and as he drew near
        to observe, the voice of the Lord came to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "saying,  \u2018I am the God of your fathers\u2014the God of Abraham,
        the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.\u2019 And Moses trembled and dared
        not look. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u2018Then the Lord said to him, \u201CTake your sandals off your
        feet, for the place where you stand is holy ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "I have surely seen the oppression of My people who are in Egypt;
        I have heard their groaning and have come down to deliver them. And now come,
        I will send you to Egypt.\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThis Moses whom they rejected, saying, \u2018Who made you a
        ruler and a judge?\u2019 is the one God sent to  be a ruler and a deliverer
        by the hand of the Angel who appeared to him in the bush. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Israel Rebels Against God'
      title: Israel Rebels Against God
      number: 36
      content: He brought them out, after he had shown wonders and signs in the land
        of Egypt, and in the Red Sea, and in the wilderness forty years.
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u201CThis is that Moses who said to the children of Israel, \u2018The
        Lord your God will raise up for you a Prophet like me from your brethren.
        Him you shall hear.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CThis is he who was in the congregation in the wilderness with
        the Angel who spoke to him on Mount Sinai, and with our fathers, the one
        who received the living oracles to give to us, "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'whom our fathers would not obey, but rejected. And in their hearts
        they turned back to Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "saying to Aaron, \u2018Make us gods to go before us; as  for this
        Moses who brought us out of the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become
        of him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And they made a calf in those days, offered sacrifices to the idol,
        and rejoiced in the works of their own hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then God turned and gave them up to worship the host of heaven, as
        it is written in the book of the Prophets:\u2018Did you offer Me slaughtered
        animals and sacrifices during forty years in the wilderness,O house of Israel?"
      comments: []
    - name: "43: God\u2019s True Tabernacle"
      title: "God\u2019s True Tabernacle"
      number: 43
      content: "You also took up the tabernacle of Moloch,And the star of your god
        Remphan,Images which you made to worship;And I will carry you away beyond
        Babylon.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201COur fathers had the tabernacle of witness in the wilderness,
        as He appointed, instructing Moses to make it according to the pattern that
        he had seen, "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'which our fathers, having received it in turn, also brought with
        Joshua into the land possessed by the Gentiles, whom God drove out before
        the face of our fathers until the days of David, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'who found favor before God and asked to find a dwelling for the God
        of Jacob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: But Solomon built Him a house.
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "\u201CHowever, the Most High does not dwell in temples made with
        hands, as the prophet says:"
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "\u2018Heaven  is My throne,And earth is My footstool.What house will
        you build for Me? says the Lord,Or what is the place of My rest?"
      comments: []
    - name: '50: Israel Resists the Holy Spirit'
      title: Israel Resists the Holy Spirit
      number: 50
      content: "Has My hand not made all these things?\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "\u201CYou  stiff-necked and uncircumcised in heart and ears! You
        always resist the Holy Spirit; as your fathers did, so do you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Which of the prophets did your fathers not persecute? And they killed
        those who foretold the coming of the Just One, of whom you now have become
        the betrayers and murderers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: Stephen the Martyr'
      title: Stephen the Martyr
      number: 53
      content: "who have received the law by the direction of angels and have not
        kept it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'When they heard these things they were cut to the heart, and they
        gnashed at him with their teeth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'But he, being full of the Holy Spirit, gazed into heaven and saw
        the glory of God, and Jesus standing at the right hand of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "and said, \u201CLook! I see the heavens opened and the Son of Man
        standing at the right hand of God!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'Then they cried out with a loud voice, stopped their ears, and ran
        at him with one accord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'and they cast him out of the city and stoned him. And the witnesses
        laid down their clothes at the feet of a young man named Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "And they stoned Stephen as he was calling on God and saying, \u201CLord
        Jesus, receive my spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "Then he knelt down and cried out with a loud voice, \u201CLord, do
        not charge them with this sin.\u201D And when he had said this, he fell asleep."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Persecutes the Church'
      title: Saul Persecutes the Church
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Saul was consenting to his death.At that time a great persecution
        arose against the church which was at Jerusalem; and they were all scattered
        throughout the regions of Judea and Samaria, except the apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And devout men carried Stephen to  his  burial, and made great lamentation
        over him.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Christ Is Preached in Samaria'
      title: Christ Is Preached in Samaria
      number: 3
      content: As for Saul, he made havoc of the church, entering every house, and
        dragging off men and women, committing them to prison.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Therefore those who were scattered went everywhere preaching the
        word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Philip went down to the city of Samaria and preached Christ
        to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the multitudes with one accord heeded the things spoken by Philip,
        hearing and seeing the miracles which he did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For unclean spirits, crying with a loud voice, came out of many who
        were possessed; and many who were paralyzed and lame were healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: "8: The Sorcerer\u2019s Profession of Faith"
      title: "The Sorcerer\u2019s Profession of Faith"
      number: 8
      content: And there was great joy in that city.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But there was a certain man called Simon, who previously practiced
        sorcery in the city and astonished the people of Samaria, claiming that he
        was someone great, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "to whom they all gave heed, from the least to the greatest, saying,
        \u201CThis man is the great power of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they heeded him because he had astonished them with his sorceries
        for a long time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when they believed Philip as he preached the things concerning
        the kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, both men and women were
        baptized. '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: The Sorcerer\u2019s Sin"
      title: "The Sorcerer\u2019s Sin"
      number: 13
      content: Then Simon himself also believed; and when he was baptized he continued
        with Philip, and was amazed, seeing the miracles and signs which were done.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now when the apostles who were at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had
        received the word of God, they sent Peter and John to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'who, when they had come down, prayed for them that they might receive
        the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For as yet He had fallen upon none of them. They had only been baptized
        in the name of the Lord Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then they laid hands on them, and they received the Holy Spirit.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And when Simon saw that through the laying on of the apostles\u2019
        hands the Holy Spirit was given, he offered them money, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "saying, \u201CGive me this power also, that anyone on whom I lay
        hands may receive the Holy Spirit.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But Peter said to him, \u201CYour money perish with you, because
        you thought that the gift of God could be purchased with money! "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You have neither part nor portion in this matter, for your heart
        is not right in the sight of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Repent therefore of this your wickedness, and pray God if perhaps
        the thought of your heart may be forgiven you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For I see that you are poisoned by bitterness and bound by iniquity.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Simon answered and said, \u201CPray to the Lord for me, that
        none of the things which you have spoken may come upon me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Christ Is Preached to an Ethiopian'
      title: Christ Is Preached to an Ethiopian
      number: 25
      content: So when they had testified and preached the word of the Lord, they
        returned to Jerusalem, preaching the gospel in many villages of the Samaritans.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Now an angel of the Lord spoke to Philip, saying, \u201CArise and
        go toward the south along the road which goes down from Jerusalem to Gaza.\u201D
        This is desert. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So he arose and went. And behold, a man of Ethiopia, a eunuch of
        great authority under Candace the queen of the Ethiopians, who had charge
        of all her treasury, and had come to Jerusalem to worship, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'was returning. And sitting in his chariot, he was reading Isaiah
        the prophet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then the Spirit said to Philip, \u201CGo near and overtake this chariot.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Philip ran to him, and heard him reading the prophet Isaiah, and
        said, \u201CDo you understand what you are reading?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said, \u201CHow can I, unless someone guides me?\u201D And
        he asked Philip to come up and sit with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "The place in the Scripture which he read was this:\u201CHe was led
        as a sheep to the slaughter;And as a lamb before its shearer is silent,So
        He opened not His mouth."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "In His humiliation His justice was taken away,And who will declare
        His generation?For His life is taken from the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "So the eunuch answered Philip and said, \u201CI ask you, of whom
        does the prophet say this, of himself or of some other man?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then Philip opened his mouth, and beginning at this Scripture, preached
        Jesus to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Now as they went down the road, they came to some water. And the
        eunuch said, \u201CSee, here  is water. What hinders me from being baptized?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Philip said, \u201CIf you believe with all your heart, you may.\u201DAnd
        he answered and said, \u201CI believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So he commanded the chariot to stand still. And both Philip and the
        eunuch went down into the water, and he baptized him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Now when they came up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord caught
        Philip away, so that the eunuch saw him no more; and he went on his way rejoicing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: But Philip was found at Azotus. And passing through, he preached in
        all the cities till he came to Caesarea.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Damascus Road: Saul Converted'
      title: 'The Damascus Road: Saul Converted'
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Saul, still breathing threats and murder against the disciples
        of the Lord, went to the high priest '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: and asked letters from him to the synagogues of Damascus, so that
        if he found any who were of the Way, whether men or women, he might bring
        them bound to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As he journeyed he came near Damascus, and suddenly a light shone
        around him from heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then he fell to the ground, and heard a voice saying to him, <JESUS>\u201CSaul,
        Saul, </JESUS><JESUS>why are you persecuting Me?\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he said, \u201CWho are You, Lord?\u201DThen the Lord said, <JESUS>\u201CI
        am Jesus, whom you are persecuting.</JESUS>  <JESUS>It </JESUS><JESUS>is</JESUS><JESUS>
        hard for you to kick against the goads.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So he, trembling and astonished, said, \u201CLord, what do You want
        me to do?\u201DThen the Lord said to him, <JESUS>\u201CArise and go into
        the city, and you will be told what you must do.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the men who journeyed with him stood speechless, hearing a voice
        but seeing no one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Saul arose from the ground, and when his eyes were opened he
        saw no one. But they led him by the hand and brought him into Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Ananias Baptizes Saul'
      title: Ananias Baptizes Saul
      number: 9
      content: And he was three days without sight, and neither ate nor drank.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now there was a certain disciple at Damascus named Ananias; and to
        him the Lord said in a vision, <JESUS>\u201CAnanias.\u201D</JESUS>And he
        said, \u201CHere I am, Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Lord said to him, <JESUS>\u201CArise and go to the street
        called Straight, and inquire at the house of Judas for </JESUS><JESUS>one</JESUS><JESUS>
        called Saul </JESUS><JESUS>of Tarsus, for behold, he is praying.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "<JESUS>And in a vision he has seen a man named Ananias coming in
        and putting </JESUS><JESUS>his</JESUS><JESUS> hand on him, so that he might
        receive his sight.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Ananias answered, \u201CLord, I have heard from many about this
        man, how much harm he has done to Your saints in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And here he has authority from the chief priests to bind all who
        call on Your name.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But the Lord said to him, <JESUS>\u201CGo, for </JESUS><JESUS>he
        is a chosen vessel of Mine to bear My name before </JESUS><JESUS>Gentiles,
        </JESUS><JESUS>kings, and the </JESUS><JESUS>children</JESUS><JESUS> of Israel.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "<JESUS>For </JESUS><JESUS>I will show him how many things he must
        suffer for My </JESUS><JESUS>name\u2019s sake.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Ananias went his way and entered the house; and laying his hands
        on him he said, \u201CBrother Saul, the Lord Jesus, who appeared to you on
        the road as you came, has sent me that you may receive your sight and be
        filled with the Holy Spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Immediately there fell from his eyes something like scales, and he
        received his sight at once; and he arose and was baptized.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Saul Preaches Christ'
      title: Saul Preaches Christ
      number: 19
      content: So when he had received food, he was strengthened. Then Saul spent
        some days with the disciples at Damascus.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Immediately he preached the Christ in the synagogues, that He is the
        Son of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then all who heard were amazed, and said, \u201CIs this not he who
        destroyed those who called on this name in Jerusalem, and has come here for
        that purpose, so that he might bring them bound to the chief priests?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Saul Escapes Death'
      title: Saul Escapes Death
      number: 22
      content: But Saul increased all the more in strength, and confounded the Jews
        who dwelt in Damascus, proving that this Jesus is the Christ.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now after many days were past, the Jews plotted to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But their plot became known to Saul. And they watched the gates day
        and night, to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Saul at Jerusalem'
      title: Saul at Jerusalem
      number: 25
      content: Then the disciples took him by night and let him down through the
        wall in a large basket.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And when Saul had come to Jerusalem, he tried to join the disciples;
        but they were all afraid of him, and did not believe that he was a disciple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But Barnabas took him and brought him to the apostles. And he declared
        to them how he had seen the Lord on the road, and that He had spoken to him,
        and how he had preached boldly at Damascus in the name of Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So he was with them at Jerusalem, coming in and going out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And he spoke boldly in the name of the Lord Jesus and disputed against
        the Hellenists, but they attempted to kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Church Prospers'
      title: The Church Prospers
      number: 30
      content: When the brethren found out, they brought him down to Caesarea and
        sent him out to Tarsus.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Aeneas Healed'
      title: Aeneas Healed
      number: 31
      content: Then the churches throughout all Judea, Galilee, and Samaria had peace
        and were edified. And walking in the fear of the Lord and in the comfort
        of the Holy Spirit, they were multiplied.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now it came to pass, as Peter went through all parts  of  the  country,
        that he also came down to the saints who dwelt in Lydda. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'There he found a certain man named Aeneas, who had been bedridden
        eight years and was paralyzed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And Peter said to him, \u201CAeneas, Jesus the Christ heals you.
        Arise and make your bed.\u201D Then he arose immediately. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Dorcas Restored to Life'
      title: Dorcas Restored to Life
      number: 35
      content: So all who dwelt at Lydda and Sharon saw him and turned to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'At Joppa there was a certain disciple named Tabitha, which is translated
        Dorcas. This woman was full of good works and charitable deeds which she
        did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'But it happened in those days that she became sick and died. When
        they had washed her, they laid her in an upper room. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And since Lydda was near Joppa, and the disciples had heard that
        Peter was there, they sent two men to him, imploring him not to delay in
        coming to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Then Peter arose and went with them. When he had come, they brought
        him to the upper room. And all the widows stood by him weeping, showing the
        tunics and garments which Dorcas had made while she was with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But Peter put them all out, and knelt down and prayed. And turning
        to the body he said, \u201CTabitha, arise.\u201D And she opened her eyes,
        and when she saw Peter she sat up. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then he gave her his hand and lifted her up; and when he had called
        the saints and widows, he presented her alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And it became known throughout all Joppa, and many believed on the
        Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: So it was that he stayed many days in Joppa with Simon, a tanner.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cornelius Sends a Delegation'
      title: Cornelius Sends a Delegation
      number: 1
      content: 'There was a certain man in Caesarea called Cornelius, a centurion
        of what was called the Italian Regiment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'a devout man and one who feared God with all his household, who gave
        alms generously to the people, and prayed to God always. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "About the ninth hour of the day he saw clearly in a vision an angel
        of God coming in and saying to him, \u201CCornelius!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And when he observed him, he was afraid, and said, \u201CWhat is
        it, lord?\u201DSo he said to him, \u201CYour prayers and your alms have come
        up for a memorial before God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now send men to Joppa, and send for Simon whose surname is Peter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He is lodging with Simon, a tanner, whose house is by the sea. He
        will tell you what you must do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when the angel who spoke to him had departed, Cornelius called
        two of his household servants and a devout soldier from among those who waited
        on him continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Peter\u2019s Vision"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Vision"
      number: 8
      content: So when he had explained all these things to them, he sent them to
        Joppa.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The next day, as they went on their journey and drew near the city,
        Peter went up on the housetop to pray, about the sixth hour. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then he became very hungry and wanted to eat; but while they made
        ready, he fell into a trance '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and saw heaven opened and an object like a great sheet bound at the
        four corners, descending to him and let down to the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'In it were all kinds of four-footed animals of the earth, wild beasts,
        creeping things, and birds of the air. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And a voice came to him, <JESUS>\u201CRise, Peter; kill and eat.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Peter said, \u201CNot so, Lord! For I have never eaten anything
        common or unclean.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And a voice spoke to him again the second time, <JESUS>\u201CWhat
        God has </JESUS><JESUS>cleansed you must not call common.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Summoned to Caesarea'
      title: Summoned to Caesarea
      number: 16
      content: This was done three times. And the object was taken up into heaven
        again.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now while Peter wondered within himself what this vision which he
        had seen meant, behold, the men who had been sent from Cornelius had made
        inquiry for Simon\u2019s house, and stood before the gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And they called and asked whether Simon, whose surname was Peter,
        was lodging there.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "While Peter thought about the vision, the Spirit said to him, \u201CBehold,
        three men are seeking you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Arise therefore, go down and go with them, doubting nothing; for
        I have sent them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Peter went down to the men who had been sent to him from Cornelius,
        and said, \u201CYes, I am he whom you seek. For what reason have you come?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And they said, \u201CCornelius the centurion, a just man, one who
        fears God and has a good reputation among all the nation of the Jews, was
        divinely instructed by a holy angel to summon you to his house, and to hear
        words from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Peter Meets Cornelius'
      title: Peter Meets Cornelius
      number: 23
      content: Then he invited them in and lodged them.On the next day Peter went
        away with them, and some brethren from Joppa accompanied him.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the following day they entered Caesarea. Now Cornelius was waiting
        for them, and had called together his relatives and close friends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'As Peter was coming in, Cornelius met him and fell down at his feet
        and worshiped him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Peter lifted him up, saying, \u201CStand up; I myself am also
        a man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And as he talked with him, he went in and found many who had come
        together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CYou know how unlawful it is for a Jewish
        man to keep company with or go to one of another nation. But God has shown
        me that I should not call any man common or unclean. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Therefore I came without objection as soon as I was sent for. I ask,
        then, for what reason have you sent for me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Cornelius said, \u201CFour days ago I was fasting until this hour;
        and at the ninth hour I prayed in my house, and behold, a man stood before
        me in bright clothing, "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "and said, \u2018Cornelius, your prayer has been heard, and your alms
        are remembered in the sight of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Send therefore to Joppa and call Simon here, whose surname is Peter.
        He is lodging in the house of Simon, a tanner, by the sea. When he comes,
        he will speak to you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "33: Preaching to Cornelius\u2019 Household"
      title: "Preaching to Cornelius\u2019 Household"
      number: 33
      content: "So I sent to you immediately, and you have done well to come. Now
        therefore, we are all present before God, to hear all the things commanded
        you by God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then Peter opened his mouth and said: \u201CIn truth I perceive that
        God shows no partiality. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But in every nation whoever fears Him and works righteousness is
        accepted by Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "The word which God sent to the children of Israel, preaching peace
        through Jesus Christ\u2014He is Lord of all\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'that word you know, which was proclaimed throughout all Judea, and
        began from Galilee after the baptism which John preached: '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'how God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit and with
        power, who went about doing good and healing all who were oppressed by the
        devil, for God was with Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And we are witnesses of all things which He did both in the land
        of the Jews and in Jerusalem, whom they killed by hanging on a tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Him God raised up on the third day, and showed Him openly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'not to all the people, but to witnesses chosen before by God, even
        to us who ate and drank with Him after He arose from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And He commanded us to preach to the people, and to testify that
        it is He who was ordained by God to  be Judge of the living and the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: The Holy Spirit Falls on the Gentiles'
      title: The Holy Spirit Falls on the Gentiles
      number: 43
      content: "To Him all the prophets witness that, through His name, whoever believes
        in Him will receive remission of sins.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'While Peter was still speaking these words, the Holy Spirit fell
        upon all those who heard the word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And those of the circumcision who believed were astonished, as many
        as came with Peter, because the gift of the Holy Spirit had been poured out
        on the Gentiles also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'For they heard them speak with tongues and magnify God.Then Peter
        answered, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "\u201CCan anyone forbid water, that these should not be baptized
        who have received the Holy Spirit just as we have?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: And he commanded them to be baptized in the name of the Lord. Then
        they asked him to stay a few days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Peter Defends God\u2019s Grace"
      title: "Peter Defends God\u2019s Grace"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the apostles and brethren who were in Judea heard that the Gentiles
        had also received the word of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when Peter came up to Jerusalem, those of the circumcision contended
        with him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "saying, \u201CYou went in to uncircumcised men and ate with them!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Peter explained it to them in order from the beginning, saying: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CI was in the city of Joppa praying; and in a trance I saw a
        vision, an object descending like a great sheet, let down from heaven by
        four corners; and it came to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When I observed it intently and considered, I saw four-footed animals
        of the earth, wild beasts, creeping things, and birds of the air. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I heard a voice saying to me, <JESUS>\u2018Rise, Peter; kill
        and eat.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But I said, \u2018Not so, Lord! For nothing common or unclean has
        at any time entered my mouth.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the voice answered me again from heaven, <JESUS>\u2018What God
        has cleansed you must not call common.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now this was done three times, and all were drawn up again into heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'At that very moment, three men stood before the house where I was,
        having been sent to me from Caesarea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Spirit told me to go with them, doubting nothing. Moreover
        these six brethren accompanied me, and we entered the man\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he told us how he had seen an angel standing in his house, who
        said to him, \u2018Send men to Joppa, and call for Simon whose surname is
        Peter, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "who will tell you words by which you and all your household will
        be saved.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And as I began to speak, the Holy Spirit fell upon them, as upon
        us at the beginning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then I remembered the word of the Lord, how He said, <JESUS>\u2018John
        indeed baptized with water, but </JESUS><JESUS>you shall be baptized with
        the Holy Spirit.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "If therefore God gave them the same gift as He  gave us when we believed
        on the Lord Jesus Christ, who was I that I could withstand God?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Barnabas and Saul at Antioch'
      title: Barnabas and Saul at Antioch
      number: 18
      content: "When they heard these things they became silent; and they glorified
        God, saying, \u201CThen God has also granted to the Gentiles repentance to
        life.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now those who were scattered after the persecution that arose over
        Stephen traveled as far as Phoenicia, Cyprus, and Antioch, preaching the
        word to no one but the Jews only. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But some of them were men from Cyprus and Cyrene, who, when they
        had come to Antioch, spoke to the Hellenists, preaching the Lord Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And the hand of the Lord was with them, and a great number believed
        and turned to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then news of these things came to the ears of the church in Jerusalem,
        and they sent out Barnabas to go as far as Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When he came and had seen the grace of God, he was glad, and encouraged
        them all that with purpose of heart they should continue with the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: For he was a good man, full of the Holy Spirit and of faith. And a
        great many people were added to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Barnabas departed for Tarsus to seek Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Relief to Judea'
      title: Relief to Judea
      number: 26
      content: And when he had found him, he brought him to Antioch. So it was that
        for a whole year they assembled with the church and taught a great many people.
        And the disciples were first called Christians in Antioch.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And in these days prophets came from Jerusalem to Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then one of them, named Agabus, stood up and showed by the Spirit
        that there was going to be a great famine throughout all the world, which
        also happened in the days of Claudius Caesar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the disciples, each according to his ability, determined to
        send relief to the brethren dwelling in Judea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: This they also did, and sent it to the elders by the hands of Barnabas
        and Saul.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Herod\u2019s Violence to the Church"
      title: "Herod\u2019s Violence to the Church"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now about that time Herod the king stretched out his hand to harass
        some from the church. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then he killed James the brother of John with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And because he saw that it pleased the Jews, he proceeded further
        to seize Peter also. Now it was during  the Days of Unleavened Bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Peter Freed from Prison'
      title: Peter Freed from Prison
      number: 4
      content: So when he had arrested him, he put him in prison, and delivered him
        to four squads of soldiers to keep him, intending to bring him before the
        people after Passover.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Peter was therefore kept in prison, but constant prayer was offered
        to God for him by the church. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when Herod was about to bring him out, that night Peter was sleeping,
        bound with two chains between two soldiers; and the guards before the door
        were keeping the prison. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now behold, an angel of the Lord stood by him, and a light shone
        in the prison; and he struck Peter on the side and raised him up, saying,
        \u201CArise quickly!\u201D And his chains fell off his hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the angel said to him, \u201CGird yourself and tie on your sandals\u201D;
        and so he did. And he said to him, \u201CPut on your garment and follow me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So he went out and followed him, and did not know that what was done
        by the angel was real, but thought he was seeing a vision. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: When they were past the first and the second guard posts, they came
        to the iron gate that leads to the city, which opened to them of its own
        accord; and they went out and went down one street, and immediately the angel
        departed from him.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And when Peter had come to himself, he said, \u201CNow I know for
        certain that the Lord has sent His angel, and has delivered me from the hand
        of Herod and from all the expectation of the Jewish people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So, when he had considered this,  he came to the house of Mary, the
        mother of John whose surname was Mark, where many were gathered together
        praying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And as Peter knocked at the door of the gate, a girl named Rhoda
        came to answer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When she recognized Peter\u2019s voice, because of her gladness she
        did not open the gate, but ran in and announced that Peter stood before the
        gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But they said to her, \u201CYou are beside yourself!\u201D Yet she
        kept insisting that it was so. So they said, \u201CIt is his angel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now Peter continued knocking; and when they opened the  door and
        saw him, they were astonished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But motioning to them with his hand to keep silent, he declared to
        them how the Lord had brought him out of the prison. And he said, \u201CGo,
        tell these things to James and to the brethren.\u201D And he departed and
        went to another place."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then, as soon as it was day, there was no small stir among the soldiers
        about what had become of Peter. '
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Herod\u2019s Violent Death"
      title: "Herod\u2019s Violent Death"
      number: 19
      content: But when Herod had searched for him and not found him, he examined
        the guards and commanded that they should be put to death.And he went down
        from Judea to Caesarea, and stayed there.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now Herod had been very angry with the people of Tyre and Sidon;
        but they came to him with one accord, and having made Blastus the king\u2019s
        personal aide their friend, they asked for peace, because their country was
        supplied with food by the king\u2019s country."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So on a set day Herod, arrayed in royal apparel, sat on his throne
        and gave an oration to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the people kept shouting, \u201CThe voice of a god and not of
        a man!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Then immediately an angel of the Lord struck him, because he did not
        give glory to God. And he was eaten by worms and died.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Barnabas and Saul Appointed'
      title: Barnabas and Saul Appointed
      number: 24
      content: But the word of God grew and multiplied.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And Barnabas and Saul returned from Jerusalem when they had fulfilled
        their ministry, and they also took with them John whose surname was Mark.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: 'Now in the church that was at Antioch there were certain prophets
        and teachers: Barnabas, Simeon who was called Niger, Lucius of Cyrene, Manaen
        who had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch, and Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "As they ministered to the Lord and fasted, the Holy Spirit said,
        \u201CNow separate to Me Barnabas and Saul for the work to which I have called
        them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Preaching in Cyprus'
      title: Preaching in Cyprus
      number: 3
      content: Then, having fasted and prayed, and laid hands on them, they sent
        them away.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So, being sent out by the Holy Spirit, they went down to Seleucia,
        and from there they sailed to Cyprus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And when they arrived in Salamis, they preached the word of God in
        the synagogues of the Jews. They also had John as their assistant.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now when they had gone through the island to Paphos, they found a
        certain sorcerer, a false prophet, a Jew whose name was Bar-Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'who was with the proconsul, Sergius Paulus, an intelligent man. This
        man called for Barnabas and Saul and sought to hear the word of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But Elymas the sorcerer (for so his name is translated) withstood
        them, seeking to turn the proconsul away from the faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Saul, who also is  called Paul, filled with the Holy Spirit,
        looked intently at him '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and said, \u201CO full of all deceit and all fraud, you son of the
        devil, you enemy of all righteousness, will you not cease perverting the
        straight ways of the Lord? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now, indeed, the hand of the Lord is upon you, and you shall
        be blind, not seeing the sun for a time.\u201DAnd immediately a dark mist
        fell on him, and he went around seeking someone to lead him by the hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: At Antioch in Pisidia'
      title: At Antioch in Pisidia
      number: 12
      content: Then the proconsul believed, when he saw what had been done, being
        astonished at the teaching of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now when Paul and his party set sail from Paphos, they came to Perga
        in Pamphylia; and John, departing from them, returned to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But when they departed from Perga, they came to Antioch in Pisidia,
        and went into the synagogue on the Sabbath day and sat down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And after the reading of the Law and the Prophets, the rulers of
        the synagogue sent to them, saying, \u201CMen and brethren, if you have any
        word of exhortation for the people, say on.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Paul stood up, and motioning with his hand said, \u201CMen of
        Israel, and you who fear God, listen: "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The God of this people Israel chose our fathers, and exalted the
        people when they dwelt as strangers in the land of Egypt, and with an uplifted
        arm He brought them out of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now for a time of about forty years He put up with their ways in
        the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And when He had destroyed seven nations in the land of Canaan, He
        distributed their land to them by allotment.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAfter that He gave them judges for about four hundred and fifty
        years, until Samuel the prophet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And afterward they asked for a king; so God gave them Saul the son
        of Kish, a man of the tribe of Benjamin, for forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And when He had removed him, He raised up for them David as king,
        to whom also He gave testimony and said, \u2018I have found David the son
        of Jesse, a man after My own heart, who will do all My will.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "From this man\u2019s seed, according to the promise, God raised up
        for Israel a Savior\u2014Jesus\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'after John had first preached, before His coming, the baptism of
        repentance to all the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And as John was finishing his course, he said, \u2018Who do you think
        I am? I am not He. But behold, there comes One after me, the sandals of whose
        feet I am not worthy to loose.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CMen and brethren, sons of the family of Abraham, and those
        among you who fear God, to you the word of this salvation has been sent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For those who dwell in Jerusalem, and their rulers, because they
        did not know Him, nor even the voices of the Prophets which are read every
        Sabbath, have fulfilled them in condemning Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And though they found no cause for death in  Him, they asked Pilate
        that He should be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now when they had fulfilled all that was written concerning Him,
        they took Him down from the tree and laid Him in a tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But God raised Him from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'He was seen for many days by those who came up with Him from Galilee
        to Jerusalem, who are His witnesses to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And we declare to you glad tidings\u2014that promise which was made
        to the fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "God has fulfilled this for us their children, in that He has raised
        up Jesus. As it is also written in the second Psalm:\u2018You are My Son,Today
        I have begotten You.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And that He raised Him from the dead, no more to return to corruption,
        He has spoken thus:\u2018I will give you the sure mercies of David.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Therefore He also says in another Psalm:\u2018You will not allow
        Your Holy One to see corruption.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CFor David, after he had served his own generation by the will
        of God, fell asleep, was buried with his fathers, and saw corruption; "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'but He whom God raised up saw no corruption. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Therefore let it be known to you, brethren, that through this Man
        is preached to you the forgiveness of sins; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and by Him everyone who believes is justified from all things from
        which you could not be justified by the law of Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Beware therefore, lest what has been spoken in the prophets come
        upon you:'
      comments: []
    - name: '41: Blessing and Conflict at Antioch'
      title: Blessing and Conflict at Antioch
      number: 41
      content: "\u2018Behold, you despisers,Marvel and perish!For I work a work in
        your days,A work which you will by no means believe,Though one were to declare
        it to you.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So when the Jews went out of the synagogue, the Gentiles begged that
        these words might be preached to them the next Sabbath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Now when the congregation had broken up, many of the Jews and devout
        proselytes followed Paul and Barnabas, who, speaking to them, persuaded them
        to continue in the grace of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'On the next Sabbath almost the whole city came together to hear the
        word of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'But when the Jews saw the multitudes, they were filled with envy;
        and contradicting and blaspheming, they opposed the things spoken by Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "Then Paul and Barnabas grew bold and said, \u201CIt was necessary
        that the word of God should be spoken to you first; but since you reject
        it, and judge yourselves unworthy of everlasting life, behold, we turn to
        the Gentiles. "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "For so the Lord has commanded us:\u2018I have set you as a light
        to the Gentiles,That you should be for salvation to the ends of the earth.\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: Now when the Gentiles heard this, they were glad and glorified the
        word of the Lord. And as many as had been appointed to eternal life believed.
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'And the word of the Lord was being spread throughout all the region. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'But the Jews stirred up the devout and prominent women and the chief
        men of the city, raised up persecution against Paul and Barnabas, and expelled
        them from their region. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'But they shook off the dust from their feet against them, and came
        to Iconium. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: And the disciples were filled with joy and with the Holy Spirit.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: At Iconium'
      title: At Iconium
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it happened in Iconium that they went together to the synagogue
        of the Jews, and so spoke that a great multitude both of the Jews and of
        the Greeks believed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But the unbelieving Jews stirred up the Gentiles and poisoned their
        minds against the brethren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Therefore they stayed there a long time, speaking boldly in the Lord,
        who was bearing witness to the word of His grace, granting signs and wonders
        to be done by their hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the multitude of the city was divided: part sided with the Jews,
        and part with the apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when a violent attempt was made by both the Gentiles and Jews,
        with their rulers, to abuse and stone them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'they became aware of it and fled to Lystra and Derbe, cities of Lycaonia,
        and to the surrounding region. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Idolatry at Lystra'
      title: Idolatry at Lystra
      number: 7
      content: And they were preaching the gospel there.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And in Lystra a certain man without strength in his feet was sitting,
        a cripple from his mother\u2019s womb, who had never walked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'This man heard Paul speaking. Paul, observing him intently and seeing
        that he had faith to be healed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "said with a loud voice, \u201CStand up straight on your feet!\u201D
        And he leaped and walked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now when the people saw what Paul had done, they raised their voices,
        saying in the Lycaonian language,  \u201CThe gods have come down to us in
        the likeness of men!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Barnabas they called Zeus, and Paul, Hermes, because he was the
        chief speaker. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Then the priest of Zeus, whose temple was in front of their city,
        brought oxen and garlands to the gates, intending to sacrifice with the multitudes.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But when the apostles Barnabas and Paul heard this, they tore their
        clothes and ran in among the multitude, crying out '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and saying, \u201CMen, why are you doing these things? We also are
        men with the same nature as you, and preach to you that you should turn from
        these useless things to the living God, who made the heaven, the earth, the
        sea, and all things that are in them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'who in bygone generations allowed all nations to walk in their own
        ways. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Nevertheless He did not leave Himself without witness, in that He
        did good, gave us rain from heaven and fruitful seasons, filling our hearts
        with food and gladness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Stoning, Escape to Derbe'
      title: Stoning, Escape to Derbe
      number: 18
      content: And with these sayings they could scarcely restrain the multitudes
        from sacrificing to them.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Jews from Antioch and Iconium came there; and having persuaded
        the multitudes, they stoned Paul and dragged him out of the city, supposing
        him to be dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Strengthening the Converts'
      title: Strengthening the Converts
      number: 20
      content: However, when the disciples gathered around him, he rose up and went
        into the city. And the next day he departed with Barnabas to Derbe.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when they had preached the gospel to that city and made many
        disciples, they returned to Lystra, Iconium, and Antioch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "strengthening the souls of the disciples, exhorting them to continue
        in the faith, and saying,  \u201CWe must through many tribulations enter
        the kingdom of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So when they had appointed elders in every church, and prayed with
        fasting, they commended them to the Lord in whom they had believed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And after they had passed through Pisidia, they came to Pamphylia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now when they had preached the word in Perga, they went down to Attalia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: From there they sailed to Antioch, where they had been commended to
        the grace of God for the work which they had completed.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now when they had come and gathered the church together, they reported
        all that God had done with them, and that He had opened the door of faith
        to the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: So they stayed there a long time with the disciples.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Conflict over Circumcision'
      title: Conflict over Circumcision
      number: 1
      content: "And certain men came down from Judea and taught the brethren, \u201CUnless
        you are circumcised according to the custom of Moses, you cannot be saved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Therefore, when Paul and Barnabas had no small dissension and dispute
        with them, they determined that Paul and Barnabas and certain others of them
        should go up to Jerusalem, to the apostles and elders, about this question.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So, being sent on their way by the church, they passed through Phoenicia
        and Samaria, describing the conversion of the Gentiles; and they caused great
        joy to all the brethren. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when they had come to Jerusalem, they were received by the church
        and the apostles and the elders; and they reported all things that God had
        done with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Jerusalem Council'
      title: The Jerusalem Council
      number: 5
      content: "But some of the sect of the Pharisees who believed rose up, saying,
        \u201CIt is necessary to circumcise them, and to command them to keep the
        law of Moses.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now the apostles and elders came together to consider this matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And when there had been much dispute, Peter rose up and said to them:
        \u201CMen and brethren, you know that a good while ago God chose among us,
        that by my mouth the Gentiles should hear the word of the gospel and believe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So God, who knows the heart, acknowledged them by giving them the
        Holy Spirit, just as He  did to us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'and made no distinction between us and them, purifying their hearts
        by faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now therefore, why do you test God by putting a yoke on the neck
        of the disciples which neither our fathers nor we were able to bear? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But we believe that through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ we
        shall be saved in the same manner as they.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then all the multitude kept silent and listened to Barnabas and Paul
        declaring how many miracles and wonders God had worked through them among
        the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And after they had become silent, James answered, saying, \u201CMen
        and brethren, listen to me: "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Simon has declared how God at the first visited the Gentiles to take
        out of them a people for His name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And with this the words of the prophets agree, just as it is written:'
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018After this I will returnAnd will rebuild the tabernacle of
        David, which has fallen down;I will rebuild its ruins,And I will set it up;"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So that the rest of mankind may seek the Lord,Even all the Gentiles
        who are called by My name,Says the Lord who does all these things.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CKnown to God from eternity are all His works. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Therefore I judge that we should not trouble those from among the
        Gentiles who are turning to God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'but that we write to them to abstain from things polluted by idols,
        from sexual immorality, from things strangled, and from blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Jerusalem Decree'
      title: The Jerusalem Decree
      number: 21
      content: "For Moses has had throughout many generations those who preach him
        in every city, being read in the synagogues every Sabbath.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then it pleased the apostles and elders, with the whole church, to
        send chosen men of their own company to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas, namely,
        Judas who was also named Barsabas, and Silas, leading men among the brethren.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: They wrote this letter by them:The apostles, the elders, and the brethren,To
        the brethren who are of the Gentiles in Antioch, Syria, and Cilicia:Greetings.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Since we have heard that some who went out from us have troubled
        you with words, unsettling your souls, saying, \u201CYou  must be circumcised
        and keep the law\u201D \u2014to whom we gave no such commandment\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'it seemed good to us, being assembled with one accord, to send chosen
        men to you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'men who have risked their lives for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'We have therefore sent Judas and Silas, who will also report the
        same things by word of mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For it seemed good to the Holy Spirit, and to us, to lay upon you
        no greater burden than these necessary things: '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Continuing Ministry in Syria'
      title: Continuing Ministry in Syria
      number: 29
      content: that you abstain from things offered to idols, from blood, from things
        strangled, and from sexual immorality. If you keep yourselves from these,
        you will do well.Farewell.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So when they were sent off, they came to Antioch; and when they had
        gathered the multitude together, they delivered the letter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When they had read it, they rejoiced over its encouragement. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now Judas and Silas, themselves being prophets also, exhorted and
        strengthened the brethren with many words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: And after they had stayed there for a time, they were sent back with
        greetings from the brethren to the apostles.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'However, it seemed good to Silas to remain there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Division over John Mark'
      title: Division over John Mark
      number: 35
      content: Paul and Barnabas also remained in Antioch, teaching and preaching
        the word of the Lord, with many others also.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then after some days Paul said to Barnabas, \u201CLet us now go back
        and visit our brethren in every city where we have preached the word of the
        Lord, and  see how they are doing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Now Barnabas was determined to take with them John called Mark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'But Paul insisted that they should not take with them the one who
        had departed from them in Pamphylia, and had not gone with them to the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Then the contention became so sharp that they parted from one another.
        And so Barnabas took Mark and sailed to Cyprus; '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'but Paul chose Silas and departed, being commended by the brethren
        to the grace of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: And he went through Syria and Cilicia, strengthening the churches.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Timothy Joins Paul and Silas'
      title: Timothy Joins Paul and Silas
      number: 1
      content: 'Then he came to Derbe and Lystra. And behold, a certain disciple
        was there, named Timothy, the son of a certain Jewish woman who believed,
        but his father was Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He was well spoken of by the brethren who were at Lystra and Iconium. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Paul wanted to have him go on with him. And he took him and circumcised
        him because of the Jews who were in that region, for they all knew that his
        father was Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And as they went through the cities, they delivered to them the decrees
        to keep, which were determined by the apostles and elders at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Macedonian Call'
      title: The Macedonian Call
      number: 5
      content: So the churches were strengthened in the faith, and increased in number
        daily.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now when they had gone through Phrygia and the region of Galatia,
        they were forbidden by the Holy Spirit to preach the word in Asia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'After they had come to Mysia, they tried to go into Bithynia, but
        the Spirit did not permit them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So passing by Mysia, they came down to Troas. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And a vision appeared to Paul in the night. A man of Macedonia stood
        and pleaded with him, saying, \u201CCome over to Macedonia and help us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Lydia Baptized at Philippi'
      title: Lydia Baptized at Philippi
      number: 10
      content: Now after he had seen the vision, immediately we sought to go to Macedonia,
        concluding that the Lord had called us to preach the gospel to them.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore, sailing from Troas, we ran a straight course to Samothrace,
        and the next day came to Neapolis, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and from there to Philippi, which is the foremost city of that part
        of Macedonia, a colony. And we were staying in that city for some days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And on the Sabbath day we went out of the city to the riverside,
        where prayer was customarily made; and we sat down and spoke to the women
        who met there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now a certain woman named Lydia heard us. She was a seller of purple
        from the city of Thyatira, who worshiped God. The Lord opened her heart to
        heed the things spoken by Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Paul and Silas Imprisoned'
      title: Paul and Silas Imprisoned
      number: 15
      content: "And when she and her household were baptized, she begged us, saying,
        \u201CIf you have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come to my house
        and stay.\u201D So she persuaded us."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now it happened, as we went to prayer, that a certain slave girl
        possessed with a spirit of divination met us, who brought her masters much
        profit by fortune-telling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "This girl followed Paul and us, and cried out, saying, \u201CThese
        men are the servants of the Most High God, who proclaim to us the way of
        salvation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And this she did for many days.But Paul, greatly annoyed, turned
        and said to the spirit, \u201CI command you in the name of Jesus Christ to
        come out of her.\u201D And he came out that very hour. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: But when her masters saw that their hope of profit was gone, they
        seized Paul and Silas and dragged them into the marketplace to the authorities.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And they brought them to the magistrates, and said, \u201CThese men,
        being Jews, exceedingly trouble our city; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "and they teach customs which are not lawful for us, being Romans,
        to receive or observe.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the multitude rose up together against them; and the magistrates
        tore off their clothes and commanded them to be beaten with rods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And when they had laid many stripes on them, they threw them into
        prison, commanding the jailer to keep them securely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: The Philippian Jailer Saved'
      title: The Philippian Jailer Saved
      number: 24
      content: Having received such a charge, he put them into the inner prison and
        fastened their feet in the stocks.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But at midnight Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns to
        God, and the prisoners were listening to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Suddenly there was a great earthquake, so that the foundations of
        the prison were shaken; and immediately all the doors were opened and everyone\u2019s
        chains were loosed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the keeper of the prison, awaking from sleep and seeing the prison
        doors open, supposing the prisoners had fled, drew his sword and was about
        to kill himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But Paul called with a loud voice, saying, \u201CDo yourself no harm,
        for we are all here.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then he called for a light, ran in, and fell down trembling before
        Paul and Silas. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he brought them out and said, \u201CSirs, what must I do to be
        saved?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So they said, \u201CBelieve on the Lord Jesus Christ, and you will
        be saved, you and your household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then they spoke the word of the Lord to him and to all who were in
        his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he took them the same hour of the night and washed their stripes.
        And immediately he and all his family were baptized. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Paul Refuses to Depart Secretly'
      title: Paul Refuses to Depart Secretly
      number: 34
      content: Now when he had brought them into his house, he set food before them;
        and he rejoiced, having believed in God with all his household.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And when it was day, the magistrates sent the officers, saying, \u201CLet
        those men go.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "So the keeper of the prison reported these words to Paul, saying,
        \u201CThe magistrates have sent to let you go. Now therefore depart, and
        go in peace.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But Paul said to them, \u201CThey have beaten us openly, uncondemned
        Romans, and have thrown us into prison. And now do they put us out secretly?
        No indeed! Let them come themselves and get us out.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And the officers told these words to the magistrates, and they were
        afraid when they heard that they were Romans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Then they came and pleaded with them and brought them out, and asked
        them to depart from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: So they went out of the prison and entered the  house  of Lydia; and
        when they had seen the brethren, they encouraged them and departed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Preaching Christ at Thessalonica'
      title: Preaching Christ at Thessalonica
      number: 1
      content: 'Now when they had passed through Amphipolis and Apollonia, they came
        to Thessalonica, where there was a synagogue of the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Paul, as his custom was, went in to them, and for three Sabbaths
        reasoned with them from the Scriptures, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "explaining and demonstrating that the Christ had to suffer and rise
        again from the dead, and saying, \u201CThis Jesus whom I preach to you is
        the Christ.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "4: Assault on Jason\u2019s House"
      title: "Assault on Jason\u2019s House"
      number: 4
      content: And some of them were persuaded; and a great multitude of the devout
        Greeks, and not a few of the leading women, joined Paul and Silas.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the Jews who were not persuaded, becoming envious, took some
        of the evil men from the marketplace, and gathering a mob, set all the city
        in an uproar and attacked the house of Jason, and sought to bring them out
        to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But when they did not find them, they dragged Jason and some brethren
        to the rulers of the city, crying out, \u201CThese who have turned the world
        upside down have come here too. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jason has harbored them, and these are all acting contrary to the
        decrees of Caesar, saying there is another king\u2014Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And they troubled the crowd and the rulers of the city when they
        heard these things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Ministering at Berea'
      title: Ministering at Berea
      number: 9
      content: So when they had taken security from Jason and the rest, they let
        them go.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the brethren immediately sent Paul and Silas away by night to
        Berea. When they arrived, they went into the synagogue of the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'These were more fair-minded than those in Thessalonica, in that they
        received the word with all readiness, and searched the Scriptures daily to 
        find  out whether these things were so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore many of them believed, and also not a few of the Greeks,
        prominent women as well as men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But when the Jews from Thessalonica learned that the word of God
        was preached by Paul at Berea, they came there also and stirred up the crowds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then immediately the brethren sent Paul away, to go to the sea; but
        both Silas and Timothy remained there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Philosophers at Athens'
      title: The Philosophers at Athens
      number: 15
      content: So those who conducted Paul brought him to Athens; and receiving a
        command for Silas and Timothy to come to him with all speed, they departed.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now while Paul waited for them at Athens, his spirit was provoked
        within him when he saw that the city was given over to idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore he reasoned in the synagogue with the Jews and with the
        Gentile worshipers, and in the marketplace daily with those who happened
        to be there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then certain Epicurean and Stoic philosophers encountered him. And
        some said, \u201CWhat does this babbler want to say?\u201DOthers said, \u201CHe
        seems to be a proclaimer of foreign gods,\u201D because he preached to them
        Jesus and the resurrection."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And they took him and brought him to the Areopagus, saying, \u201CMay
        we know what this new doctrine is of which you speak? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For you are bringing some strange things to our ears. Therefore we
        want to know what these things mean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Addressing the Areopagus'
      title: Addressing the Areopagus
      number: 21
      content: For all the Athenians and the foreigners who were there spent their
        time in nothing else but either to tell or to hear some new thing.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Paul stood in the midst of the Areopagus and said, \u201CMen
        of Athens, I perceive that in all things you are very religious; "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'for as I was passing through and considering the objects of your
        worship, I even found an altar with this inscription:TO THE UNKNOWN GOD.Therefore,
        the One whom you worship without knowing, Him I proclaim to you: '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CGod, who made the world and everything in it, since He is Lord
        of heaven and earth, does not dwell in temples made with hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Nor is He worshiped with men\u2019s hands, as though He needed anything,
        since He gives to all life, breath, and all things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And He has made from one blood every nation of men to dwell on all
        the face of the earth, and has determined their preappointed times and the
        boundaries of their dwellings, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'so that they should seek the Lord, in the hope that they might grope
        for Him and find Him, though He is not far from each one of us; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "for in Him we live and move and have our being, as also some of your
        own poets have said, \u2018For we are also His offspring.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Therefore, since we are the offspring of God, we ought not to think
        that the Divine Nature is like gold or silver or stone, something shaped
        by art and man\u2019s devising. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Truly, these times of ignorance God overlooked, but now commands
        all men everywhere to repent, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "because He has appointed a day on which He will judge the world in
        righteousness by the Man whom He has ordained. He has given assurance of
        this to all by raising Him from the dead.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And when they heard of the resurrection of the dead, some mocked,
        while others said, \u201CWe will hear you again on this matter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So Paul departed from among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: However, some men joined him and believed, among them Dionysius the
        Areopagite, a woman named Damaris, and others with them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ministering at Corinth'
      title: Ministering at Corinth
      number: 1
      content: 'After these things Paul departed from Athens and went to Corinth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he found a certain Jew named Aquila, born in Pontus, who had
        recently come from Italy with his wife Priscilla (because Claudius had commanded
        all the Jews to depart from Rome); and he came to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So, because he was of the same trade, he stayed with them and worked;
        for by occupation they were tentmakers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And he reasoned in the synagogue every Sabbath, and persuaded both
        Jews and Greeks.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Silas and Timothy had come from Macedonia, Paul was compelled
        by the Spirit, and testified to the Jews that Jesus is the Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But when they opposed him and blasphemed, he shook his garments and
        said to them, \u201CYour blood be upon your own heads; I am clean. From now
        on I will go to the Gentiles.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he departed from there and entered the house of a certain man
        named Justus, one who worshiped God, whose house was next door to the synagogue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Then Crispus, the ruler of the synagogue, believed on the Lord with
        all his household. And many of the Corinthians, hearing, believed and were
        baptized.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now the Lord spoke to Paul in the night by a vision, <JESUS>\u201CDo
        not be afraid, but speak, and do not keep silent;</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "<JESUS>for I am with you, and no one will attack you to hurt you;
        for I have many people in this city.\u201D</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And he continued there a year and six months, teaching the word of
        God among them.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Gallio was proconsul of Achaia, the Jews with one accord rose
        up against Paul and brought him to the judgment seat, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "saying, \u201CThis fellow persuades men to worship God contrary to
        the law.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And when Paul was about to open his mouth, Gallio said to the Jews,
        \u201CIf it were a matter of wrongdoing or wicked crimes, O Jews, there would
        be reason why I should bear with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But if it is a question of words and names and your own law, look
        to  it yourselves; for I do not want to be a judge of such matters.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he drove them from the judgment seat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Paul Returns to Antioch'
      title: Paul Returns to Antioch
      number: 17
      content: Then all the Greeks took Sosthenes, the ruler of the synagogue, and
        beat him before the judgment seat. But Gallio took no notice of these things.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Paul still remained a good while. Then he took leave of the brethren
        and sailed for Syria, and Priscilla and Aquila were with him. He had his
        hair cut off at Cenchrea, for he had taken a vow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he came to Ephesus, and left them there; but he himself entered
        the synagogue and reasoned with the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When they asked him to stay a longer time with them, he did not consent, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but took leave of them, saying, \u201CI must by all means keep this
        coming feast in Jerusalem; but I will return again to you, God willing.\u201D
        And he sailed from Ephesus."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And when he had landed at Caesarea, and gone up and greeted the church,
        he went down to Antioch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Ministry of Apollos'
      title: Ministry of Apollos
      number: 23
      content: After he had spent some time there, he departed and went over the
        region of Galatia and Phrygia in order, strengthening all the disciples.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now a certain Jew named Apollos, born at Alexandria, an eloquent
        man and mighty in the Scriptures, came to Ephesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'This man had been instructed in the way of the Lord; and being fervent
        in spirit, he spoke and taught accurately the things of the Lord, though
        he knew only the baptism of John. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So he began to speak boldly in the synagogue. When Aquila and Priscilla
        heard him, they took him aside and explained to him the way of God more accurately. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And when he desired to cross to Achaia, the brethren wrote, exhorting
        the disciples to receive him; and when he arrived, he greatly helped those
        who had believed through grace; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: for he vigorously refuted the Jews publicly, showing from the Scriptures
        that Jesus is the Christ.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul at Ephesus'
      title: Paul at Ephesus
      number: 1
      content: 'And it happened, while Apollos was at Corinth, that Paul, having
        passed through the upper regions, came to Ephesus. And finding some disciples '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "he said to them, \u201CDid you receive the Holy Spirit when you believed?\u201DSo
        they said to him, \u201CWe have not so much as heard whether there is a Holy
        Spirit.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CInto what then were you baptized?\u201DSo
        they said, \u201CInto John\u2019s baptism.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Paul said, \u201CJohn indeed baptized with a baptism of repentance,
        saying to the people that they should believe on Him who would come after
        him, that is, on Christ Jesus.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When they heard this, they were baptized in the name of the Lord
        Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when Paul had laid hands on them, the Holy Spirit came upon them,
        and they spoke with tongues and prophesied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Now the men were about twelve in all.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he went into the synagogue and spoke boldly for three months,
        reasoning and persuading concerning the things of the kingdom of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But when some were hardened and did not believe, but spoke evil of
        the Way before the multitude, he departed from them and withdrew the disciples,
        reasoning daily in the school of Tyrannus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Miracles Glorify Christ'
      title: Miracles Glorify Christ
      number: 10
      content: And this continued for two years, so that all who dwelt in Asia heard
        the word of the Lord Jesus, both Jews and Greeks.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now God worked unusual miracles by the hands of Paul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'so that even handkerchiefs or aprons were brought from his body to
        the sick, and the diseases left them and the evil spirits went out of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then some of the itinerant Jewish exorcists took it upon themselves
        to call the name of the Lord Jesus over those who had evil spirits, saying,
        \u201CWe exorcise you by the Jesus whom Paul preaches.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Also there were seven sons of Sceva, a Jewish chief priest, who did
        so.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the evil spirit answered and said, \u201CJesus I know, and Paul
        I know; but who are you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the man in whom the evil spirit was leaped on them, overpowered
        them, and prevailed against them, so that they fled out of that house naked
        and wounded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'This became known both to all Jews and Greeks dwelling in Ephesus;
        and fear fell on them all, and the name of the Lord Jesus was magnified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And many who had believed came confessing and telling their deeds. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Also, many of those who had practiced magic brought their books together
        and burned them in the sight of all. And they counted up the value of them,
        and it totaled fifty thousand pieces of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Riot at Ephesus'
      title: The Riot at Ephesus
      number: 20
      content: So the word of the Lord grew mightily and prevailed.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When these things were accomplished, Paul purposed in the Spirit,
        when he had passed through Macedonia and Achaia, to go to Jerusalem, saying,
        \u201CAfter I have been there, I must also see Rome.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So he sent into Macedonia two of those who ministered to him, Timothy
        and Erastus, but he himself stayed in Asia for a time.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And about that time there arose a great commotion about the Way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For a certain man named Demetrius, a silversmith, who made silver
        shrines of Diana, brought no small profit to the craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He called them together with the workers of similar occupation, and
        said: \u201CMen, you know that we have our prosperity by this trade. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Moreover you see and hear that not only at Ephesus, but throughout
        almost all Asia, this Paul has persuaded and turned away many people, saying
        that they are not gods which are made with hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So not only is this trade of ours in danger of falling into disrepute,
        but also the temple of the great goddess Diana may be despised and her magnificence
        destroyed, whom all Asia and the world worship.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now when they heard this, they were full of wrath and cried out,
        saying, \u201CGreat is Diana of the Ephesians!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So the whole city was filled with confusion, and rushed into the
        theater with one accord, having seized Gaius and Aristarchus, Macedonians,
        Paul\u2019s travel companions. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And when Paul wanted to go in to the people, the disciples would
        not allow him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then some of the officials of Asia, who were his friends, sent to
        him pleading that he would not venture into the theater. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Some therefore cried one thing and some another, for the assembly
        was confused, and most of them did not know why they had come together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And they drew Alexander out of the multitude, the Jews putting him
        forward. And Alexander motioned with his hand, and wanted to make his defense
        to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But when they found out that he was a Jew, all with one voice cried
        out for about two hours, \u201CGreat is Diana of the Ephesians!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And when the city clerk had quieted the crowd, he said: \u201CMen
        of Ephesus, what man is there who does not know that the city of the Ephesians
        is temple guardian of the great goddess Diana, and of the image which fell
        down from Zeus? "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Therefore, since these things cannot be denied, you ought to be quiet
        and do nothing rashly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For you have brought these men here who are neither robbers of temples
        nor blasphemers of your goddess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Therefore, if Demetrius and his fellow craftsmen have a case against
        anyone, the courts are open and there are proconsuls. Let them bring charges
        against one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But if you have any other inquiry to make, it shall be determined
        in the lawful assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "For we are in danger of being called in question for today\u2019s
        uproar, there being no reason which we may give to account for this disorderly
        gathering.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: And when he had said these things, he dismissed the assembly.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Journeys in Greece'
      title: Journeys in Greece
      number: 1
      content: 'After the uproar had ceased, Paul called the disciples to himself,
        embraced them, and departed to go to Macedonia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now when he had gone over that region and encouraged them with many
        words, he came to Greece '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and stayed three months. And when the Jews plotted against him as
        he was about to sail to Syria, he decided to return through Macedonia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Sopater of Berea accompanied him to Asia\u2014also Aristarchus
        and Secundus of the Thessalonians, and Gaius of Derbe, and Timothy, and Tychicus
        and Trophimus of Asia. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'These men, going ahead, waited for us at Troas. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Ministering at Troas'
      title: Ministering at Troas
      number: 6
      content: But we sailed away from Philippi after the Days of Unleavened Bread,
        and in five days joined them at Troas, where we stayed seven days.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now on the first day of the week, when the disciples came together
        to break bread, Paul, ready to depart the next day, spoke to them and continued
        his message until midnight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'There were many lamps in the upper room where they were gathered
        together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And in a window sat a certain young man named Eutychus, who was sinking
        into a deep sleep. He was overcome by sleep; and as Paul continued speaking,
        he fell down from the third story and was taken up dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Paul went down, fell on him, and embracing him said, \u201CDo
        not trouble yourselves, for his life is in him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now when he had come up, had broken bread and eaten, and talked a
        long while, even till daybreak, he departed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: From Troas to Miletus'
      title: From Troas to Miletus
      number: 12
      content: And they brought the young man in alive, and they were not a little
        comforted.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then we went ahead to the ship and sailed to Assos, there intending
        to take Paul on board; for so he had given orders, intending himself to go
        on foot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when he met us at Assos, we took him on board and came to Mitylene. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'We sailed from there, and the next day came opposite Chios. The following
        day we arrived at Samos and stayed at Trogyllium. The next day we came to
        Miletus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Ephesian Elders Exhorted'
      title: The Ephesian Elders Exhorted
      number: 16
      content: For Paul had decided to sail past Ephesus, so that he would not have
        to spend time in Asia; for he was hurrying to be at Jerusalem, if possible,
        on the Day of Pentecost.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'From Miletus he sent to Ephesus and called for the elders of the
        church. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And when they had come to him, he said to them: \u201CYou know, from
        the first day that I came to Asia, in what manner I always lived among you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'serving the Lord with all humility, with many tears and trials which
        happened to me by the plotting of the Jews; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'how I kept back nothing that was helpful, but proclaimed it to you,
        and taught you publicly and from house to house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'testifying to Jews, and also to Greeks, repentance toward God and
        faith toward our Lord Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And see, now I go bound in the spirit to Jerusalem, not knowing the
        things that will happen to me there, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'except that the Holy Spirit testifies in every city, saying that
        chains and tribulations await me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: But none of these things move me; nor do I count my life dear to myself,
        so that I may finish my race with joy, and the ministry which I received
        from the Lord Jesus, to testify to the gospel of the grace of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CAnd indeed, now I know that you all, among whom I have gone
        preaching the kingdom of God, will see my face no more. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Therefore I testify to you this day that I am  innocent of the blood
        of all men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For I have not shunned to declare to you the whole counsel of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Therefore take heed to yourselves and to all the flock, among which
        the Holy Spirit has made you overseers, to shepherd the church of God which
        He purchased with His own blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For I know this, that after my departure savage wolves will come
        in among you, not sparing the flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Also from among yourselves men will rise up, speaking perverse things,
        to draw away the disciples after themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Therefore watch, and remember that for three years I did not cease
        to warn everyone night and day with tears.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CSo now, brethren, I commend you to God and to the word of His
        grace, which is able to build you up and give you an inheritance among all
        those who are sanctified. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "I have coveted no one\u2019s silver or gold or apparel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Yes, you yourselves know that these hands have provided for my necessities,
        and for those who were with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "I have shown you in every way, by laboring like this, that you must
        support the weak. And remember the words of the Lord Jesus, that He said,
        <JESUS>\u2018It is more blessed to give than to receive.\u2019</JESUS> \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And when he had said these things, he knelt down and prayed with
        them all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then they all wept freely, and fell on Paul\u2019s neck and kissed
        him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: sorrowing most of all for the words which he spoke, that they would
        see his face no more. And they accompanied him to the ship.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warnings on the Journey to Jerusalem'
      title: Warnings on the Journey to Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass, that when we had departed from them and set
        sail, running a straight course we came to Cos, the following day to Rhodes,
        and from there to Patara. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And finding a ship sailing over to Phoenicia, we went aboard and
        set sail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When we had sighted Cyprus, we passed it on the left, sailed to Syria,
        and landed at Tyre; for there the ship was to unload her cargo. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And finding disciples, we stayed there seven days. They told Paul
        through the Spirit not to go up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When we had come to the end of those days, we departed and went on
        our way; and they all accompanied us, with wives and children, till we  were
        out of the city. And we knelt down on the shore and prayed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: When we had taken our leave of one another, we boarded the ship, and
        they returned home.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when we had finished our voyage from Tyre, we came to Ptolemais,
        greeted the brethren, and stayed with them one day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "On the next day we who were Paul\u2019s companions departed and came
        to Caesarea, and entered the house of Philip the evangelist, who was one
        of the seven, and stayed with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now this man had four virgin daughters who prophesied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And as we stayed many days, a certain prophet named Agabus came down
        from Judea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When he had come to us, he took Paul\u2019s belt, bound his own hands
        and feet, and said, \u201CThus says the Holy Spirit, \u2018So shall the Jews
        at Jerusalem bind the man who owns this belt, and deliver him into the hands
        of the Gentiles.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now when we heard these things, both we and those from that place
        pleaded with him not to go up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Paul answered, \u201CWhat do you mean by weeping and breaking
        my heart? For I am ready not only to be bound, but also to die at Jerusalem
        for the name of the Lord Jesus.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Paul Urged to Make Peace'
      title: Paul Urged to Make Peace
      number: 14
      content: "So when he would not be persuaded, we ceased, saying, \u201CThe will
        of the Lord be done.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And after those days we packed and went up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Also some of the disciples from Caesarea went with us and brought
        with them a certain Mnason of Cyprus, an early disciple, with whom we were
        to lodge.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And when we had come to Jerusalem, the brethren received us gladly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'On the following day Paul went in with us to James, and all the elders
        were present. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When he had greeted them, he told in detail those things which God
        had done among the Gentiles through his ministry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And when they heard it, they glorified the Lord. And they said to
        him, \u201CYou see, brother, how many myriads of Jews there are who have
        believed, and they are all zealous for the law; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'but they have been informed about you that you teach all the Jews
        who are among the Gentiles to forsake Moses, saying that they ought not to
        circumcise their children nor to walk according to the customs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'What then? The assembly must certainly meet, for they will hear that
        you have come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Therefore do what we tell you: We have four men who have taken a
        vow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Take them and be purified with them, and pay their expenses so that
        they may shave their heads, and that all may know that those things of which
        they were informed concerning you are nothing, but that you yourself also
        walk orderly and keep the law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Arrested in the Temple'
      title: Arrested in the Temple
      number: 25
      content: "But concerning the Gentiles who believe, we have written and decided
        that they should observe no such thing, except that they should keep themselves
        from things offered to idols, from blood, from things strangled, and from
        sexual immorality.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Then Paul took the men, and the next day, having been purified with
        them, entered the temple to announce the expiration of the days of purification,
        at which time an offering should be made for each one of them.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now when the seven days were almost ended, the Jews from Asia, seeing
        him in the temple, stirred up the whole crowd and laid hands on him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "crying out, \u201CMen of Israel, help! This is the man who teaches
        all men everywhere against the people, the law, and this place; and furthermore
        he also brought Greeks into the temple and has defiled this holy place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: (For they had previously seen Trophimus the Ephesian with him in the
        city, whom they supposed that Paul had brought into the temple.)
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And all the city was disturbed; and the people ran together, seized
        Paul, and dragged him out of the temple; and immediately the doors were shut. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now as they were seeking to kill him, news came to the commander
        of the garrison that all Jerusalem was in an uproar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He immediately took soldiers and centurions, and ran down to them.
        And when they saw the commander and the soldiers, they stopped beating Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then the commander came near and took him, and commanded him to be
        bound with two chains; and he asked who he was and what he had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And some among the multitude cried one thing and some another.So
        when he could not ascertain the truth because of the tumult, he commanded
        him to be taken into the barracks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'When he reached the stairs, he had to be carried by the soldiers
        because of the violence of the mob. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: Addressing the Jerusalem Mob'
      title: Addressing the Jerusalem Mob
      number: 36
      content: "For the multitude of the people followed after, crying out, \u201CAway
        with him!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then as Paul was about to be led into the barracks, he said to the
        commander, \u201CMay I speak to you?\u201DHe replied, \u201CCan you speak
        Greek? "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Are you not the Egyptian who some time ago stirred up a rebellion
        and led the four thousand assassins out into the wilderness?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But Paul said, \u201CI am a Jew from Tarsus, in Cilicia, a citizen
        of no mean city; and I implore you, permit me to speak to the people.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: So when he had given him permission, Paul stood on the stairs and
        motioned with his hand to the people. And when there was a great silence,
        he spoke to them in the Hebrew language, saying,
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CBrethren and fathers, hear my defense before you now.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when they heard that he spoke to them in the Hebrew language,
        they kept all the more silent.Then he said: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI am indeed a Jew, born in Tarsus of Cilicia, but brought up
        in this city at the feet of Gamaliel, taught according to the strictness
        of our fathers\u2019 law, and was zealous toward God as you all are today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I persecuted this Way to the death, binding and delivering into prisons
        both men and women, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: as also the high priest bears me witness, and all the council of the
        elders, from whom I also received letters to the brethren, and went to Damascus
        to bring in chains even those who were there to Jerusalem to be punished.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CNow it happened, as I journeyed and came near Damascus at about
        noon, suddenly a great light from heaven shone around me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I fell to the ground and heard a voice saying to me, <JESUS>\u2018Saul,
        Saul, why are you persecuting Me?\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So I answered, \u2018Who are You, Lord?\u2019 And He said to me,
        <JESUS>\u2018I am Jesus of Nazareth, whom you are persecuting.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CAnd those who were with me indeed saw the light and were afraid,
        but they did not hear the voice of Him who spoke to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So I said, \u2018What shall I do, Lord?\u2019 And the Lord said to
        me, <JESUS>\u2018Arise and go into Damascus, and there you will be told all
        things which are appointed for you to do.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And since I could not see for the glory of that light, being led by
        the hand of those who were with me, I came into Damascus.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThen a certain Ananias, a devout man according to the law,
        having a good testimony with all the Jews who dwelt there,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "came to me; and he stood and said to me, \u2018Brother Saul, receive
        your sight.\u2019 And at that same hour I looked up at him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said, \u2018The God of our fathers has chosen you that you
        should know His will, and see the Just One, and hear the voice of His mouth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For you will be His witness to all men of what you have seen and
        heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And now why are you waiting? Arise and be baptized, and wash away
        your sins, calling on the name of the Lord.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CNow it happened, when I returned to Jerusalem and was praying
        in the temple, that I was in a trance "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and saw Him saying to me, <JESUS>\u2018Make haste and get out of
        Jerusalem quickly, for they will not receive your testimony concerning Me.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So I said, \u2018Lord, they know that in every synagogue I imprisoned
        and beat those who believe on You. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And when the blood of Your martyr Stephen was shed, I also was standing
        by consenting to his death, and guarding the clothes of those who were killing
        him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "21: Paul\u2019s Roman Citizenship"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Roman Citizenship"
      number: 21
      content: "Then He said to me, <JESUS>\u2018Depart, </JESUS><JESUS>for I will
        send you far from here to the Gentiles.\u2019</JESUS> \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And they listened to him until this word, and then they raised their
        voices and said, \u201CAway with such a fellow from the earth, for he is
        not fit to live!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then, as they cried out and tore off their clothes and threw dust
        into the air, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'the commander ordered him to be brought into the barracks, and said
        that he should be examined under scourging, so that he might know why they
        shouted so against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And as they bound him with thongs, Paul said to the centurion who
        stood by, \u201CIs it lawful for you to scourge a man who is a Roman, and
        uncondemned?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When the centurion heard that, he went and told the commander, saying,
        \u201CTake care what you do, for this man is a Roman.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the commander came and said to him, \u201CTell me, are you a
        Roman?\u201DHe said, \u201CYes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The commander answered, \u201CWith a large sum I obtained this citizenship.\u201DAnd
        Paul said, \u201CBut I was born a  citizen.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Sanhedrin Divided'
      title: The Sanhedrin Divided
      number: 29
      content: Then immediately those who were about to examine him withdrew from
        him; and the commander was also afraid after he found out that he was a Roman,
        and because he had bound him.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: The next day, because he wanted to know for certain why he was accused
        by the Jews, he released him from his bonds, and commanded the chief priests
        and all their council to appear, and brought Paul down and set him before
        them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Then Paul, looking earnestly at the council, said, \u201CMen and
        brethren, I have lived in all good conscience before God until this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the high priest Ananias commanded those who stood by him to strike
        him on the mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Paul said to him, \u201CGod will strike you, you whitewashed
        wall! For you sit to judge me according to the law, and do you command me
        to be struck contrary to the law?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And those who stood by said, \u201CDo you revile God\u2019s high
        priest?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Paul said, \u201CI did not know, brethren, that he was the high
        priest; for it is written, \u2018You shall not speak evil of a ruler of your
        people.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But when Paul perceived that one part were Sadducees and the other
        Pharisees, he cried out in the council, \u201CMen and brethren, I am a Pharisee,
        the son of a Pharisee; concerning the hope and resurrection of the dead I
        am being judged!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when he had said this, a dissension arose between the Pharisees
        and the Sadducees; and the assembly was divided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For Sadducees say that there is no resurrection\u2014and no angel
        or spirit; but the Pharisees confess both. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then there arose a loud outcry. And the scribes of the Pharisees\u2019
        party arose and protested, saying, \u201CWe find no evil in this man; but
        if a spirit or an angel has spoken to him, let us not fight against God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Plot Against Paul'
      title: The Plot Against Paul
      number: 10
      content: Now when there arose a great dissension, the commander, fearing lest
        Paul might be pulled to pieces by them, commanded the soldiers to go down
        and take him by force from among them, and bring him into the barracks.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the following night the Lord stood by him and said, <JESUS>\u201CBe
        of good cheer, Paul; for as you have testified for Me in </JESUS><JESUS>Jerusalem,
        so you must also bear witness at </JESUS><JESUS>Rome.\u201D</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when it was day, some of the Jews banded together and bound themselves
        under an oath, saying that they would neither eat nor drink till they had
        killed Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now there were more than forty who had formed this conspiracy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They came to the chief priests and elders, and said, \u201CWe have
        bound ourselves under a great oath that we will eat nothing until we have
        killed Paul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now you, therefore, together with the council, suggest to the commander
        that he be brought down to you tomorrow, as though you were going to make
        further inquiries concerning him; but we are ready to kill him before he
        comes near.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So when Paul\u2019s sister\u2019s son heard of their ambush, he went
        and entered the barracks and told Paul. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Paul called one of the centurions to him and said, \u201CTake
        this young man to the commander, for he has something to tell him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So he took him and brought him to the commander and said, \u201CPaul
        the prisoner called me to him and asked me to bring this young man to you.
        He has something to say to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the commander took him by the hand, went aside, and asked privately,
        \u201CWhat is it that you have to tell me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he said, \u201CThe Jews have agreed to ask that you bring Paul
        down to the council tomorrow, as though they were going to inquire more fully
        about him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But do not yield to them, for more than forty of them lie in wait
        for him, men who have bound themselves by an oath that they will neither
        eat nor drink till they have killed him; and now they are ready, waiting
        for the promise from you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Sent to Felix'
      title: Sent to Felix
      number: 22
      content: "So the commander let the young man depart, and commanded him, \u201CTell
        no one that you have revealed these things to me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he called for two centurions, saying, \u201CPrepare two hundred
        soldiers, seventy horsemen, and two hundred spearmen to go to Caesarea at
        the third hour of the night; "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "and provide mounts to set Paul on, and bring him safely to Felix
        the governor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He wrote a letter in the following manner:'
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Claudius Lysias,To the most excellent governor Felix:Greetings.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'This man was seized by the Jews and was about to be killed by them.
        Coming with the troops I rescued him, having learned that he was a Roman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And when I wanted to know the reason they accused him, I brought
        him before their council. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I found out that he was accused concerning questions of their law,
        but had nothing charged against him deserving of death or chains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And when it was told me that the Jews lay in wait for the man, I sent
        him immediately to you, and also commanded his accusers to state before you
        the charges against him.Farewell.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then the soldiers, as they were commanded, took Paul and brought
        him by night to Antipatris. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The next day they left the horsemen to go on with him, and returned
        to the barracks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When they came to Caesarea and had delivered the letter to the governor,
        they also presented Paul to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And when the governor had read it, he asked what province he was
        from. And when he understood that he  was from Cilicia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "he said, \u201CI will hear you when your accusers also have come.\u201D
        And he commanded him to be kept in Herod\u2019s Praetorium."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Accused of Sedition'
      title: Accused of Sedition
      number: 1
      content: Now after five days Ananias the high priest came down with the elders
        and a certain orator named Tertullus. These gave evidence to the governor
        against Paul.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And when he was called upon, Tertullus began his accusation, saying:
        \u201CSeeing that through you we enjoy great peace, and prosperity is being
        brought to this nation by your foresight, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'we accept it always and in all places, most noble Felix, with all
        thankfulness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Nevertheless, not to be tedious to you any further, I beg you to
        hear, by your courtesy, a few words from us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For we have found this man a plague, a creator of dissension among
        all the Jews throughout the world, and a ringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He even tried to profane the temple, and we seized him, and wanted
        to judge him according to our law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But the commander Lysias came by and with great violence took him
        out of our hands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "commanding his accusers to come to you. By examining him yourself
        you may ascertain all these things of which we accuse him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Defense Before Felix'
      title: The Defense Before Felix
      number: 9
      content: And the Jews also assented, maintaining that these things were so.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Paul, after the governor had nodded to him to speak, answered:
        \u201CInasmuch as I know that you have been for many years a judge of this
        nation, I do the more cheerfully answer for myself, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'because you may ascertain that it is no more than twelve days since
        I went up to Jerusalem to worship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they neither found me in the temple disputing with anyone nor
        inciting the crowd, either in the synagogues or in the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Nor can they prove the things of which they now accuse me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But this I confess to you, that according to the Way which they call
        a sect, so I worship the God of my fathers, believing all things which are
        written in the Law and in the Prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I have hope in God, which they themselves also accept, that there
        will be a resurrection of the dead, both of the just and the unjust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: This being so, I myself always strive to have a conscience without
        offense toward God and men.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CNow after many years I came to bring alms and offerings to
        my nation, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'in the midst of which some Jews from Asia found me purified in the
        temple, neither with a mob nor with tumult. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They ought to have been here before you to object if they had anything
        against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Or else let those who are here themselves say if they found any wrongdoing
        in me while I stood before the council, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Felix Procrastinates'
      title: Felix Procrastinates
      number: 21
      content: "unless it  is for this one statement which I cried out, standing
        among them, \u2018Concerning the resurrection of the dead I am being judged
        by you this day.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But when Felix heard these things, having more accurate knowledge
        of the  Way, he adjourned the proceedings and said, \u201CWhen Lysias the
        commander comes down, I will make a decision on your case.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So he commanded the centurion to keep Paul and to let him have liberty,
        and told him not to forbid any of his friends to provide for or visit him.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And after some days, when Felix came with his wife Drusilla, who
        was Jewish, he sent for Paul and heard him concerning the faith in Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now as he reasoned about righteousness, self-control, and the judgment
        to come, Felix was afraid and answered, \u201CGo away for now; when I have
        a convenient time I will call for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Meanwhile he also hoped that money would be given him by Paul, that
        he might release him. Therefore he sent for him more often and conversed
        with him.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: But after two years Porcius Festus succeeded Felix; and Felix, wanting
        to do the Jews a favor, left Paul bound.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Appeals to Caesar'
      title: Paul Appeals to Caesar
      number: 1
      content: 'Now when Festus had come to the province, after three days he went
        up from Caesarea to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the high priest and the chief men of the Jews informed him against
        Paul; and they petitioned him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "asking a favor against him, that he would summon him to Jerusalem\u2014while
        they lay in ambush along the road to kill him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Festus answered that Paul should be kept at Caesarea, and that
        he himself was going there shortly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CTherefore,\u201D he said, \u201Clet those who have authority
        among you go down with me and accuse this man, to see if there is any fault
        in him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And when he had remained among them more than ten days, he went down
        to Caesarea. And the next day, sitting on the judgment seat, he commanded
        Paul to be brought. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When he had come, the Jews who had come down from Jerusalem stood
        about and laid many serious complaints against Paul, which they could not
        prove, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "while he answered for himself, \u201CNeither against the law of the
        Jews, nor against the temple, nor against Caesar have I offended in anything
        at all.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Festus, wanting to do the Jews a favor, answered Paul and said,
        \u201CAre you willing to go up to Jerusalem and there be judged before me
        concerning these things?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Paul said, \u201CI stand at Caesar\u2019s judgment seat, where
        I ought to be judged. To the Jews I have done no wrong, as you very well
        know. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For if I am an offender, or have committed anything deserving of
        death, I do not object to dying; but if there is nothing in these things
        of which these men accuse me, no one can deliver me to them. I appeal to
        Caesar.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Paul Before Agrippa'
      title: Paul Before Agrippa
      number: 12
      content: "Then Festus, when he had conferred with the council, answered, \u201CYou
        have appealed to Caesar? To Caesar you shall go!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And after some days King Agrippa and Bernice came to Caesarea to
        greet Festus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When they had been there many days, Festus laid Paul\u2019s case
        before the king, saying: \u201CThere is a certain man left a prisoner by
        Felix, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'about whom the chief priests and the elders of the Jews informed
        me, when I was in Jerusalem, asking for a judgment against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "To them I answered, \u2018It is not the custom of the Romans to deliver
        any man to destruction before the accused meets the accusers face to face,
        and has opportunity to answer for himself concerning the charge against him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore when they had come together, without any delay, the next
        day I sat on the judgment seat and commanded the man to be brought in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When the accusers stood up, they brought no accusation against him
        of such things as I supposed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'but had some questions against him about their own religion and about
        a certain Jesus, who had died, whom Paul affirmed to be alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And because I was uncertain of such questions, I asked whether he
        was willing to go to Jerusalem and there be judged concerning these matters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But when Paul appealed to be reserved for the decision of Augustus,
        I commanded him to be kept till I could send him to Caesar.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Agrippa said to Festus, \u201CI also would like to hear the
        man myself.\u201D\u201CTomorrow,\u201D he said, \u201Cyou shall hear him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So the next day, when Agrippa and Bernice had come with great pomp,
        and had entered the auditorium with the commanders and the prominent men
        of the city, at Festus\u2019 command Paul was brought in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Festus said: \u201CKing Agrippa and all the men who are here
        present with us, you see this man about whom the whole assembly of the Jews
        petitioned me, both at Jerusalem and here, crying out that he was not fit
        to live any longer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But when I found that he had committed nothing deserving of death,
        and that he himself had appealed to Augustus, I decided to send him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I have nothing certain to write to my lord concerning him. Therefore
        I have brought him out before you, and especially before you, King Agrippa,
        so that after the examination has taken place I may have something to write. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For it seems to me unreasonable to send a prisoner and not to specify
        the charges against him.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Early Life"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Early Life"
      number: 1
      content: "Then Agrippa said to Paul, \u201CYou are permitted to speak for yourself.\u201DSo
        Paul stretched out his hand and answered for himself: "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI think myself happy, King Agrippa, because today I shall answer
        for myself before you concerning all the things of which I am accused by
        the Jews, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: especially because you are expert in all customs and questions which
        have to do with the Jews. Therefore I beg you to hear me patiently.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CMy manner of life from my youth, which was spent from the beginning
        among my own nation at Jerusalem, all the Jews know. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They knew me from the first, if they were willing to testify, that
        according to the strictest sect of our religion I lived a Pharisee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And now I stand and am judged for the hope of the promise made by
        God to our fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "To this promise  our twelve tribes, earnestly serving God  night
        and day, hope to attain. For this hope\u2019s sake, King Agrippa, I am accused
        by the Jews. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Why should it be thought incredible by you that God raises the dead?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIndeed, I myself thought I must do many things contrary to
        the name of Jesus of Nazareth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'This I also did in Jerusalem, and many of the saints I shut up in
        prison, having received authority from the chief priests; and when they were
        put to death, I cast my vote against them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Paul Recounts His Conversion'
      title: Paul Recounts His Conversion
      number: 11
      content: And I punished them often in every synagogue and compelled them to
        blaspheme; and being exceedingly enraged against them, I persecuted them
        even to foreign cities.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhile thus occupied, as I journeyed to Damascus with authority
        and commission from the chief priests, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'at midday, O king, along the road I saw a light from heaven, brighter
        than the sun, shining around me and those who journeyed with me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And when we all had fallen to the ground, I heard a voice speaking
        to me and saying in the Hebrew language, <JESUS>\u2018Saul, Saul, why are
        you persecuting Me? </JESUS><JESUS>It is</JESUS><JESUS> hard for you to kick
        against the goads.\u2019</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So I said, \u2018Who are You, Lord?\u2019 And He said, <JESUS>\u2018I
        am Jesus, whom you are persecuting.</JESUS>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '<JESUS>But rise and stand on your feet; for I have appeared to you
        for this purpose, </JESUS><JESUS>to make you a minister and a witness both
        of the things which you have seen and of the things which I will yet reveal
        to you.</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '<JESUS>I will </JESUS><JESUS>deliver you from the </JESUS><JESUS>Jewish</JESUS><JESUS>
        people, as well as </JESUS><JESUS>from</JESUS><JESUS> the Gentiles, </JESUS><JESUS>to
        whom I </JESUS><JESUS>now</JESUS><JESUS> send you,</JESUS>  '
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Paul\u2019s Post-Conversion Life"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Post-Conversion Life"
      number: 18
      content: "<JESUS>to open their eyes, </JESUS><JESUS>in order</JESUS>  <JESUS>to
        turn </JESUS><JESUS>them</JESUS><JESUS> from darkness to light, and </JESUS><JESUS>from</JESUS><JESUS>
        the power of Satan to God, </JESUS><JESUS>that they may receive forgiveness
        of sins and </JESUS><JESUS>an inheritance among those who are </JESUS><JESUS>sanctified</JESUS><JESUS>
        by faith in Me.\u2019</JESUS>"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CTherefore, King Agrippa, I was not disobedient to the heavenly
        vision, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'but declared first to those in Damascus and in Jerusalem, and throughout
        all the region of Judea, and then to the Gentiles, that they should repent,
        turn to God, and do works befitting repentance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For these reasons the Jews seized me in the temple and tried to kill
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore, having obtained help from God, to this day I stand, witnessing
        both to small and great, saying no other things than those which the prophets
        and Moses said would come\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Agrippa Parries Paul\u2019s Challenge"
      title: "Agrippa Parries Paul\u2019s Challenge"
      number: 23
      content: "that the Christ would suffer, that He would be the first to rise
        from the dead, and would proclaim light to the Jewish people and to the Gentiles.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Now as he thus made his defense, Festus said with a loud voice, \u201CPaul,
        you are beside yourself! Much learning is driving you mad!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But he said, \u201CI am not mad, most noble Festus, but speak the
        words of truth and reason. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For the king, before whom I also speak freely, knows these things;
        for I am convinced that none of these things escapes his attention, since
        this thing was not done in a corner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "King Agrippa, do you believe the prophets? I know that you do believe.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Agrippa said to Paul, \u201CYou almost persuade me to become
        a Christian.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And Paul said, \u201CI would to God that not only you, but also all
        who hear me today, might become both almost and altogether such as I am,
        except for these chains.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When he had said these things, the king stood up, as well as the
        governor and Bernice and those who sat with them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "and when they had gone aside, they talked among themselves, saying,
        \u201CThis man is doing nothing deserving of death or chains.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Agrippa said to Festus, \u201CThis man might have been set free
        if he had not appealed to Caesar.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Voyage to Rome Begins'
      title: The Voyage to Rome Begins
      number: 1
      content: 'And when it was decided that we should sail to Italy, they delivered
        Paul and some other prisoners to one named Julius, a centurion of the Augustan
        Regiment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So, entering a ship of Adramyttium, we put to sea, meaning to sail
        along the coasts of Asia. Aristarchus, a Macedonian of Thessalonica, was
        with us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And the next day we landed at Sidon. And Julius treated Paul kindly
        and gave him liberty to go to his friends and receive care. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When we had put to sea from there, we sailed under the  shelter 
        of Cyprus, because the winds were contrary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when we had sailed over the sea which is off Cilicia and Pamphylia,
        we came to Myra, a  city of Lycia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: There the centurion found an Alexandrian ship sailing to Italy, and
        he put us on board.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When we had sailed slowly many days, and arrived with difficulty
        off Cnidus, the wind not permitting us to proceed, we sailed under the  shelter 
        of  Crete off Salmone. '
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Paul\u2019s Warning Ignored"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Warning Ignored"
      number: 8
      content: Passing it with difficulty, we came to a place called Fair Havens,
        near the city of Lasea.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now when much time had been spent, and sailing was now dangerous
        because the Fast was already over, Paul advised them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "saying, \u201CMen, I perceive that this voyage will end with disaster
        and much loss, not only of the cargo and ship, but also our lives.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Nevertheless the centurion was more persuaded by the helmsman and
        the owner of the ship than by the things spoken by Paul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: In the Tempest'
      title: In the Tempest
      number: 12
      content: And because the harbor was not suitable to winter in, the majority
        advised to set sail from there also, if by any means they could reach Phoenix,
        a harbor of Crete opening toward the southwest and northwest, and winter
        there.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When the south wind blew softly, supposing that they had obtained
        their desire, putting out to sea, they sailed close by Crete. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But not long after, a tempestuous head wind arose, called Euroclydon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So when the ship was caught, and could not head into the wind, we
        let her drive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And running under the  shelter  of an island called Clauda, we secured
        the skiff with difficulty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'When they had taken it on board, they used cables to undergird the
        ship; and fearing lest they should run aground on the Syrtis Sands, they
        struck sail and so were driven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And because we were exceedingly tempest-tossed, the next day they
        lightened the ship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "On the third day  we threw the ship\u2019s tackle overboard with
        our own hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Now when neither sun nor stars appeared for many days, and no small
        tempest beat on us, all hope that we would be saved was finally given up.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But after long abstinence from food, then Paul stood in the midst
        of them and said, \u201CMen, you should have listened to me, and not have
        sailed from Crete and incurred this disaster and loss. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And now I urge you to take heart, for there will be no loss of life
        among you, but only of the ship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For there stood by me this night an angel of the God to whom I belong
        and whom I serve, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "saying, \u2018Do not be afraid, Paul; you must be brought before
        Caesar; and indeed God has granted you all those who sail with you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Therefore take heart, men, for I believe God that it will be just
        as it was told me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "However, we must run aground on a certain island.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now when the fourteenth night had come, as we were driven up and
        down in the Adriatic Sea, about midnight the sailors sensed that they were
        drawing near some land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And they took soundings and found it to be twenty fathoms; and when
        they had gone a little farther, they took soundings again and found it to
        be fifteen fathoms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then, fearing lest we should run aground on the rocks, they dropped
        four anchors from the stern, and prayed for day to come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And as the sailors were seeking to escape from the ship, when they
        had let down the skiff into the sea, under pretense of putting out anchors
        from the prow, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Paul said to the centurion and the soldiers, \u201CUnless these men
        stay in the ship, you cannot be saved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Then the soldiers cut away the ropes of the skiff and let it fall
        off.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And as day was about to dawn, Paul implored them all to take food,
        saying, \u201CToday is the fourteenth day you have waited and continued without
        food, and eaten nothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Therefore I urge you to take nourishment, for this is for your survival,
        since not a hair will fall from the head of any of you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And when he had said these things, he took bread and gave thanks
        to God in the presence of them all; and when he had broken it he began to
        eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then they were all encouraged, and also took food themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And in all we were two hundred and seventy-six persons on the ship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: Shipwrecked on Malta'
      title: Shipwrecked on Malta
      number: 38
      content: So when they had eaten enough, they lightened the ship and threw out
        the wheat into the sea.
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'When it was day, they did not recognize the land; but they observed
        a bay with a beach, onto which they planned to run the ship if possible. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And they let go the anchors and left them in the sea, meanwhile loosing
        the rudder ropes; and they hoisted the mainsail to the wind and made for
        shore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: But striking a place where two seas met, they ran the ship aground;
        and the prow stuck fast and remained immovable, but the stern was being broken
        up by the violence of the waves.
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "And the soldiers\u2019 plan was to kill the prisoners, lest any of
        them should swim away and escape. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'But the centurion, wanting to save Paul, kept them from their purpose,
        and commanded that those who could swim should jump overboard first and get
        to land, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: and the rest, some on boards and some on parts of the ship. And so
        it was that they all escaped safely to land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Ministry on Malta"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Ministry on Malta"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now when they had escaped, they then found out that the island was
        called Malta. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the natives showed us unusual kindness; for they kindled a fire
        and made us all welcome, because of the rain that was falling and because
        of the cold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But when Paul had gathered a bundle of sticks and laid them on the
        fire, a viper came out because of the heat, and fastened on his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So when the natives saw the creature hanging from his hand, they
        said to one another, \u201CNo doubt this man is a murderer, whom, though
        he has escaped the sea, yet justice does not allow to live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But he shook off the creature into the fire and suffered no harm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: However, they were expecting that he would swell up or suddenly fall
        down dead. But after they had looked for a long time and saw no harm come
        to him, they changed their minds and said that he was a god.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In that region there was an estate of the leading citizen of the
        island, whose name was Publius, who received us and entertained us courteously
        for three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it happened that the father of Publius lay sick of a fever and
        dysentery. Paul went in to him and prayed, and he laid his hands on him and
        healed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So when this was done, the rest of those on the island who had diseases
        also came and were healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Arrival at Rome'
      title: Arrival at Rome
      number: 10
      content: They also honored us in many ways; and when we departed, they provided
        such things as were necessary.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'After three months we sailed in an Alexandrian ship whose figurehead
        was the Twin Brothers, which had wintered at the island. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And landing at Syracuse, we stayed three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'From there we circled round and reached Rhegium. And after one day
        the south wind blew; and the next day we came to Puteoli, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'where we found brethren, and were invited to stay with them seven
        days. And so we went toward Rome. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And from there, when the brethren heard about us, they came to meet
        us as far as Appii Forum and Three Inns. When Paul saw them, he thanked God
        and took courage.
      comments: []
    - name: "16: Paul\u2019s Ministry at Rome"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Ministry at Rome"
      number: 16
      content: Now when we came to Rome, the centurion delivered the prisoners to
        the captain of the guard; but Paul was permitted to dwell by himself with
        the soldier who guarded him.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And it came to pass after three days that Paul called the leaders
        of the Jews together. So when they had come together, he said to them: \u201CMen
        and brethren, though I have done nothing against our people or the customs
        of our fathers, yet I was delivered as a prisoner from Jerusalem into the
        hands of the Romans, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'who, when they had examined me, wanted to let me go, because there
        was no cause for putting me to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But when the Jews spoke against it,  I was compelled to appeal to
        Caesar, not that I had anything of which to accuse my nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For this reason therefore I have called for you, to see you and speak
        with you, because for the hope of Israel I am bound with this chain.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CWe neither received letters from Judea
        concerning you, nor have any of the brethren who came reported or spoken
        any evil of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But we desire to hear from you what you think; for concerning this
        sect, we know that it is spoken against everywhere.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So when they had appointed him a day, many came to him at his lodging,
        to whom he explained and solemnly testified of the kingdom of God, persuading
        them concerning Jesus from both the Law of Moses and the Prophets, from morning
        till evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And some were persuaded by the things which were spoken, and some
        disbelieved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So when they did not agree among themselves, they departed after
        Paul had said one word: \u201CThe Holy Spirit spoke rightly through Isaiah
        the prophet to our fathers, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "saying,\u2018Go to this people and say:\u201CHearing you will hear,
        and shall not understand;And seeing you will see, and not perceive;"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "For the hearts of this people have grown dull.Their ears are hard
        of hearing,And their eyes they have closed,Lest they should see with their
        eyes and hear with their ears,Lest they should understand with their hearts
        and turn,So that I should heal them.\u201D \u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CTherefore let it be known to you that the salvation of God
        has been sent to the Gentiles, and they will hear it!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: And when he had said these words, the Jews departed and had a great
        dispute among themselves.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Paul dwelt two whole years in his own rented house, and received
        all who came to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: preaching the kingdom of God and teaching the things which concern
        the Lord Jesus Christ with all confidence, no one forbidding him.
      comments: []
